1
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,009
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

2
00:00:18,010 --> 00:00:20,609
(Lee Kwang Soo)

3
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:22,709
(Kim Woo Bin)

4
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:24,949
(Doh Kyung Soo)

5
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:28,050
(This program contains indirect advertisements.)

6
00:00:29,590 --> 00:00:31,860
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

7
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:35,360
(Their second technical training in a horse ranch)

8
00:00:35,860 --> 00:00:38,660
(A sanctuary where retired racehorses roam freely)

9
00:00:39,130 --> 00:00:41,300
(Set against 462,810m² of endless grasslands)

10
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:44,269
(The first task given to the trainees)

11
00:00:44,270 --> 00:00:46,270
(Kyung Soo, what are you doing instead of picking up poop?)

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:49,410
(Picking up horse manure for compost)

13
00:00:49,910 --> 00:00:52,880
(By now, the trainees are experts at dealing with poop.)

14
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:55,479
(They finish collecting the manure in no time.)

15
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:56,750
Make sure you get me from behind.

16
00:00:57,150 --> 00:01:00,920
(While they're at it, they take photos to help sell the manure.)

17
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:03,620
(And they're assigned to a partner horse.)

18
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:05,959
(Spending some bonding time with his partner horse)

19
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:07,660
(Achick!)

20
00:01:08,730 --> 00:01:11,900
(Bonding with a horse isn't so easy.)

21
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:13,460
What is his name?

22
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:15,969
- Morris.
- Morris?

23
00:01:15,970 --> 00:01:18,569
(This time, it's Kyung Soo and Morris' turn.)

24
00:01:18,570 --> 00:01:19,870
He's quite mischievous.

25
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,710
He tests people at first.

26
00:01:22,370 --> 00:01:25,240
(Can he win over the picky Morris?)

27
00:01:25,910 --> 00:01:27,579
(As he learned, he tries bonding by turning his back.)

28
00:01:27,580 --> 00:01:29,010
Right. You're following what you learned.

29
00:01:29,150 --> 00:01:30,980
That's great. Hug his neck.

30
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:36,289
(Morris accepts Kyung Soo's touch.)

31
00:01:36,290 --> 00:01:37,320
Morris.

32
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:41,089
- Gosh, that's amazing.
- He is...

33
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:42,589
(He seems to like his partner.)

34
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:44,830
He likes people, doesn't he?

35
00:01:45,630 --> 00:01:47,630
It's not that he likes people. He likes Kyung Soo.

36
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,870
Do you want to approach him? Go ahead, Kwang Soo.

37
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,339
Let Kwang Soo...

38
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:54,469
(Move out of the way for a minute.)

39
00:01:54,470 --> 00:01:57,140
(He sneaks up in front of Morris.)

40
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:59,609
(Suddenly turning gentle)

41
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:01,049
(Snorting)

42
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:02,309
(Thud)

43
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:04,720
(Go away)

44
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:07,119
(Suddenly becoming polite)

45
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,149
Watch where you hit.

46
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:09,150
Goodness.

47
00:02:09,151 --> 00:02:10,790
(Humph)

48
00:02:10,890 --> 00:02:12,519
I was lifted off the ground for a second.

49
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,520
Seriously?

50
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:15,160
Let's go.

51
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:20,969
(Kyung Soo and Morris begin the leading training.)

52
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:22,930
(Exclaiming)

53
00:02:26,370 --> 00:02:28,169
(Kyung Soo and Morris look like a painting together.)

54
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:29,339
Come on.

55
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:30,340
There.

56
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:34,009
(Well done, Morris.)

57
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:37,519
(What do you think of your partner horse?)

58
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,920
He's amazing.

59
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:43,320
It really feels like we're moving as one.

60
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:46,260
It's fun.

61
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:48,529
Honestly, I'm being careful about everything right now.

62
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:49,729
(Kwang Soo's partner horse, John Snow)

63
00:02:49,730 --> 00:02:51,130
I can't even raise my voice.

64
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:54,130
To be honest, I'm scared out of my mind.

65
00:02:56,330 --> 00:02:58,400
If he tells me to lie down flat, I'd probably do it.

66
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:04,439
(Kwang Soo has completely surrendered to John Snow.)

67
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,440
Let's go.

68
00:03:05,610 --> 00:03:07,239
(Jolt)

69
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,780
I'll wait a bit and give him a break.

70
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:10,980
By the way,

71
00:03:11,850 --> 00:03:13,220
are the horses assigned to us for good?

72
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:15,290
(Isn't there another horse?)

73
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,350
Let's go.

74
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,559
Goodness.

75
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,920
Come on. I seriously can't wait anymore.

76
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:21,460
Come on, let's go. Achick.

77
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,889
(He doesn't even budge.)

78
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:25,730
Could you call the boss for me?

79
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:28,530
I have to call in the parents. This won't work.

80
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,030
- What's the problem?
- Achick.

81
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:34,270
I don't think John Snow is listening to him.

82
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:35,709
Look at all the hair he's shedding.

83
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:38,180
(Meanwhile, Kyung Soo remains perfectly at peace.)

84
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:42,549
- He's moving.
- Let's go.

85
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:43,749
(Just when he finally starts moving)

86
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,319
(Whining)

87
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,380
Gosh.

88
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:50,419
No, don't go into the field. He'll eat all the tangerines.

89
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:52,519
The field belongs to the head of the women's association. Come out.

90
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,520
Come on.

91
00:03:53,521 --> 00:03:55,330
It's not here. It's not our grass.

92
00:03:55,930 --> 00:03:56,930
Let's go.

93
00:03:57,260 --> 00:03:58,330
It belongs to the head of the women's association.

94
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,330
Sir, could you...

95
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,670
- Achick.
- Pull him out now.

96
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,899
Go ahead and eat.

97
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:07,909
(Meanwhile, Kyung Soo and Morris...)

98
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:08,940
You're eating well.

99
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:15,409
(They're enjoying some quality time together.)

100
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:18,049
He really chooses what he eats.

101
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:19,550
- Only the tastiest grass?
- Yes.

102
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:22,650
He sniffs around to search.

103
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,990
When it's not the right one, he spits it out.

104
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:26,590
He keeps looking...

105
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,060
until he finds grass that's tender.

106
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:34,000
Only the soft and tasty blades that are good to chew.

107
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,430
Listen to his chewing.

108
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,100
It must be so good.

109
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,270
He's so gentle.

110
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:45,009
(Sighing)

111
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:46,010
(Meanwhile, nothing has changed for him.)

112
00:04:46,011 --> 00:04:47,380
Has he been assigned to a partner horse?

113
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:51,449
(Kwang Soo goes as far as scouting for another partner.)

114
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:52,520
That one looks small.

115
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:54,420
He's small and cute.

116
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:58,260
(He spots an adorable little horse with Sung Joon.)

117
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,390
Sung Joon.

118
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:01,290
Sung Joon.

119
00:05:01,590 --> 00:05:02,590
Yes?

120
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:03,590
Could you...

121
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:07,030
Could you switch partners...

122
00:05:07,230 --> 00:05:09,499
(With me?)

123
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,530
Achick.

124
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,940
(He desperately wants Sung Joon's partner.)

125
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,169
This is Yeonjin.

126
00:05:15,170 --> 00:05:16,369
- Yeonjin?
- Yes.

127
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:17,470
I really like him.

128
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:20,009
- Could you switch with me?
- Yes.

129
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:21,049
Thank you.

130
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:22,379
(He changes to Yeonjin without 1 second of hesitation.)

131
00:05:22,380 --> 00:05:23,609
Let's go. Achick.

132
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:24,620
Let's go, Yeonjin.

133
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:27,520
My goodness, he's so obedient.

134
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:31,489
(John Snow moves immediately at Sung Joon's order.)

135
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:33,560
I've been begging him to go for one hour.

136
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:36,690
(Feeling let down)

137
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:37,900
Yeonjin.

138
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:41,629
(It's okay because Yeonjin is with me now.)

139
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:45,000
This is exactly my ideal type.

140
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:47,000
I'm serious.

141
00:05:47,570 --> 00:05:49,410
The one I've always dreamed of. Let's go.

142
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:52,409
(Finally forming a real bond)

143
00:05:52,410 --> 00:05:55,179
(Caressing)

144
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:58,320
(They each grow closer to their partner.)

145
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,689
(After many ups and downs, everyone bonds with their horse.)

146
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:04,120
Now comes the more important part.

147
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:07,760
We're going to move our horses to a pasture with better grazing.

148
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,759
There's no grass left inside this paddock, right?

149
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,030
- Right.
- They must've eaten it all.

150
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,960
They graze inside this paddock.

151
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:16,769
Three days later, they move over here to graze.

152
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,900
This is how you get them accustomed to it.

153
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,870
Here's what we have to do.

154
00:06:20,970 --> 00:06:22,870
Whenever we rotate pastures,

155
00:06:22,970 --> 00:06:24,810
we do basic pest control first.

156
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:28,409
We spray for ticks and insects, and the horses come right over.

157
00:06:28,410 --> 00:06:30,350
Let's move them together.

158
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:33,079
Morris, let's go.

159
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,849
(Everyone leads their partner horse to the new pasture.)

160
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:35,850
Achick.

161
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:38,820
Achick.

162
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:41,930
(Kyung Soo leads Morris.)

163
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:43,660
Slowly.

164
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,500
Slowly.

165
00:06:46,730 --> 00:06:49,530
(They're still perfectly in sync.)

166
00:06:50,530 --> 00:06:52,640
Let's go. Come on.

167
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,809
(Being dragged)

168
00:06:55,810 --> 00:06:56,970
Gosh.

169
00:06:57,470 --> 00:06:58,480
(Grunting)

170
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:02,779
(If Morris uses his strength, there would be no stopping him.)

171
00:07:02,780 --> 00:07:03,850
No.

172
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:06,180
Slowly.

173
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:09,449
(On the other hand, Kwang Soo switched partners.)

174
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:11,360
Did you see him slow down when I told him to?

175
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,789
You're a good match with Yeonjin.

176
00:07:13,790 --> 00:07:14,790
I know.

177
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:17,130
All right, run.

178
00:07:18,030 --> 00:07:19,630
Run. Go.

179
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:21,500
Do we run?

180
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,970
(Jogging, sprinting)

181
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:26,540
(Moaning)

182
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,910
His legs are so long.

183
00:07:29,010 --> 00:07:30,070
You're going too fast.

184
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:32,810
You're going way too fast.

185
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:36,380
(Keeping up with a running horse isn't easy.)

186
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:38,350
Morris, let's go slowly.

187
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,350
No, it's this way.

188
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:44,019
Come on.

189
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,690
(When the horse doesn't listen, guide him in a circle.)

190
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:49,490
(Just when he seems to cooperate again)

191
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:51,530
(Being dragged again)

192
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,660
Achick.

193
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:54,830
Hey!

194
00:07:56,230 --> 00:07:57,330
You're good.

195
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,400
Is it tasty?

196
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,310
Let's go, Morris.

197
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,409
Gosh, no.

198
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:09,010
(Walking with the horse while leading and being led)

199
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:10,850
We're here.

200
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:13,420
(Where they arrive)

201
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:21,190
(A wide, lush pasture stretches out ahead.)

202
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:29,930
- Watch, Kwang Soo.
- Okay.

203
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:31,640
From here on, they're free.

204
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,000
Hop.

205
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,240
Once you let him loose...

206
00:08:35,241 --> 00:08:36,869
(The excited horses dash into the pasture.)

207
00:08:36,870 --> 00:08:38,010
Let him go.

208
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:40,310
Hop.

209
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:41,310
(Hopping off)

210
00:08:48,990 --> 00:08:50,690
Gosh, it's really green.

211
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:56,159
It feels like letting juvenile dairy cows loose.

212
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,230
It's like letting them out to pasture.

213
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:02,870
(They arrived at a new grazing field.)

214
00:09:04,330 --> 00:09:05,400
Stop him.

215
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,310
Stop him.

216
00:09:08,770 --> 00:09:10,809
(Arthur suddenly makes a run for the entrance.)

217
00:09:10,810 --> 00:09:11,810
He's trying to get out.

218
00:09:11,811 --> 00:09:13,640
Hop. No!

219
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,380
He's going home.

220
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,910
Come back in here.

221
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:19,150
(They barely stop him from getting out.)

222
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:22,819
Is he trying to go home?

223
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:24,490
- He wants to go back.
- Why?

224
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,960
When horses are familiar with a place,

225
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:28,089
they try to stay there.

226
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:29,530
But this is a new environment for him.

227
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:33,200
He keeps trying to go back home...

228
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:35,670
even though there's more and better grass here.

229
00:09:36,970 --> 00:09:38,770
He's so busy eating.

230
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:42,310
(Watching to see how well the horses adjust to the new pasture)

231
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:45,039
(The horses roam peacefully across the meadow.)

232
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,040
Goodness.

233
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:47,640
(Then their homing instinct kicks in.)

234
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:52,820
(What?)

235
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,220
(Charging forward at full speed)

236
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:58,520
(The trainees desperately try to stop them.)

237
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,220
What do we do?

238
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,590
(The horses slip past them like the wind.)

239
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,360
(Flustered)

240
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,670
(In a panic)

241
00:10:10,730 --> 00:10:11,740
Stop them.

242
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,340
(Breaking through the ranch staff's attempt to hold them back)

243
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:16,610
(They escape.)

244
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:20,940
Gosh, this is an emergency.

245
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,720
Run. We must catch them.

246
00:10:28,990 --> 00:10:30,020
It's an emergency.

247
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,189
We need to go and catch them.

248
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:33,559
(The ranch staff and production crew chase after them.)

249
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:34,730
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

250
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:37,130
Let's go and catch them.

251
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:41,369
(The horses are running so fast.)

252
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:42,470
How do we catch them?

253
00:10:43,430 --> 00:10:44,530
Don't go.

254
00:10:44,870 --> 00:10:46,369
(All he can do is say empty words of persuasion.)

255
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:47,370
What...

256
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:52,340
(The horses speed farther away, leaving the desperate calls behind.)

257
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:55,709
- There they are.
- They're running so fast.

258
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:56,810
What do we do?

259
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:01,589
Let me take a look.

260
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:03,519
They're about to get to the other side.

261
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:04,590
The pasture is this way.

262
00:11:05,420 --> 00:11:06,819
- We'd better hurry and catch them.
- We're in trouble.

263
00:11:06,820 --> 00:11:08,130
Please get the car ready in the front.

264
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,789
(It doesn't look like they're heading home.)

265
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:11,930
Get the car ready in the front.

266
00:11:16,730 --> 00:11:19,670
(The horses gallop freely.)

267
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:28,550
(Human effort seems insignificant compared to the horse's speed.)

268
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,120
Please go quickly.

269
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:38,290
(The humans must do everything possible to stop them.)

270
00:11:39,190 --> 00:11:40,360
- There they are.
- There they are.

271
00:11:42,690 --> 00:11:43,960
We got Arthur.

272
00:11:48,070 --> 00:11:49,170
How many are there here?

273
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:51,700
Catch Arthur, okay?

274
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,869
Keep driving straight.

275
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,370
(They find Arthur trespassing in someone else's field.)

276
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:59,940
(One runaway horse is successfully captured.)

277
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,710
Where did the yellow horse go?

278
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:03,610
One horse went this way.

279
00:12:04,410 --> 00:12:06,350
(The field team searches for the other horses.)

280
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,350
Could you call the helicopter camera team?

281
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:10,950
Wait.

282
00:12:10,951 --> 00:12:13,060
- There he is.
- There he is.

283
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,960
I got you.

284
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:19,230
(The little troublemaker is grazing, unaware of his worried dad.)

285
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:21,530
Achick. Come on.

286
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:24,230
Where are they?

287
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,170
We should contact the helicopter camera team.

288
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,669
- This way is the pasture.
- Yes.

289
00:12:28,670 --> 00:12:30,139
- This way?
- Yes.

290
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,810
(The drone control room is also in a state of emergency.)

291
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:34,580
The hackberry tree forest... They're at the end of the ranch.

292
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,510
- How many ropes do we have?
- We have one.

293
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:40,020
There should be one more in the car behind us.

294
00:12:40,580 --> 00:12:41,720
For four horses...

295
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,450
A total of six.

296
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:45,320
- I see four horses.
- Yes.

297
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,419
I think these are the last ones.

298
00:12:47,420 --> 00:12:48,430
(They located the remaining four horses.)

299
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:49,760
Go.

300
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:52,500
- Go. That's right.
- There's one more horse.

301
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:54,560
He's coming.

302
00:12:55,530 --> 00:12:56,929
Are these the only four that left?

303
00:12:56,930 --> 00:12:57,930
Yes.

304
00:12:59,470 --> 00:13:02,470
Sir, the horses are in front of the restaurant.

305
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:03,940
Right now...

306
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,380
Then we're missing one.

307
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,710
We caught one horse by the entrance.

308
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,110
Really? Did a total of seven horses go back in?

309
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:12,550
- There's 1 horse over there.
- Is there 1 inside?

310
00:13:13,220 --> 00:13:15,089
- There is. So we have everyone.
- Yes.

311
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:17,350
They caught Haesol there, so we have all seven.

312
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,820
(Finally, they can relax.)

313
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:23,859
- What is going on?
- We already caught Haesol.

314
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:24,960
(The great escape that caught everyone off guard)

315
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,100
I got him.

316
00:13:26,101 --> 00:13:28,729
(With the humans handling the situation)

317
00:13:28,730 --> 00:13:29,730
Where are they?

318
00:13:30,730 --> 00:13:31,870
The horses are coming.

319
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:34,240
How do we steer him?

320
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,810
(Thanks to the horses' homing instinct)

321
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:43,650
(All of them were safely captured quickly.)

322
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:47,720
Gosh, that's a relief.

323
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:52,520
Does this happen...

324
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:56,130
I'd rather clean up poop.

325
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:59,700
(Energy from horses that ordinary people can hardly handle)

326
00:14:01,930 --> 00:14:04,699
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

327
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:07,239
(Lee Kwang Soo)

328
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,409
(Kim Woo Bin)

329
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:11,680
(Doh Kyung Soo)

330
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:18,550
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

331
00:14:18,780 --> 00:14:20,279
- They're coming.
- They also left last week.

332
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:21,889
- They're coming back.
- They're coming.

333
00:14:21,890 --> 00:14:23,689
Those troublemakers.

334
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:24,750
Guys.

335
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,559
A moment ago...

336
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:29,860
(The horses and the field team return near the pasture.)

337
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:32,960
(Laughing)

338
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,230
Look at them sweating.

339
00:14:36,430 --> 00:14:37,430
I know.

340
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:39,770
There's a blast of hot air coming out of his nose.

341
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,640
Do horses sweat?

342
00:14:41,940 --> 00:14:43,270
Yes, they sweat a lot.

343
00:14:44,070 --> 00:14:45,510
- Is this all sweat?
- It is.

344
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:50,180
(Their little adventure was intense enough to soak them in sweat.)

345
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:52,150
It feels like...

346
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,549
we made some memories.

347
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:58,620
So I don't feel bad about it.

348
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:00,090
It feels like...

349
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:02,390
we went through something big together.

350
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,470
People in Jeju often see horses around.

351
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,740
The man in the dump truck earlier actually raise horses.

352
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,799
So whenever his horses escape,

353
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,870
people report it right away.

354
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:18,810
You get calls from your neighbors immediately.

355
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:22,550
I'm grateful for that, but I also feel sorry for causing trouble.

356
00:15:23,650 --> 00:15:25,780
I heard that cars blocked the road for us.

357
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:28,049
They drove by and said,

358
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:29,589
"They went this way."

359
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:33,289
(We sincerely apologize once again to the local residents...)

360
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:35,089
It was like something out of a police movie.

361
00:15:35,090 --> 00:15:36,730
(and thank everyone who helped us resolve the situation.)

362
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:41,460
(It's time to spray the horses with tick repellent.)

363
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,200
Hold on.

364
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:45,770
This is too small for you.

365
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:48,170
(Thud)

366
00:15:48,610 --> 00:15:49,610
I'm sorry.

367
00:15:49,610 --> 00:15:50,610
Seriously.

368
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:52,279
- I was trying...
- It doesn't make sense.

369
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,280
Sorry about that.

370
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:54,909
That's hard to believe.

371
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,510
(It's hard not to think that he did it on purpose.)

372
00:15:58,050 --> 00:15:59,579
Sir, do we treat all of them?

373
00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:00,580
Of course.

374
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:03,750
Kyung Soo, this is a tick. Come and look.

375
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:07,060
- What? Is it the round thing?
- Yes.

376
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,929
- Ticks that are the size of a bean.
- Yes.

377
00:16:08,930 --> 00:16:10,360
- Do you see it? Look.
- Yes.

378
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,460
- Look at this.
- You're right.

379
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Look at the tick.

380
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:18,130
It drank blood.

381
00:16:18,670 --> 00:16:22,070
Egrets come and pick them off.

382
00:16:23,740 --> 00:16:26,810
(Kwang Soo pumps the sprayer to apply the repellent.)

383
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,250
Sir...

384
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,750
Sir?

385
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,390
Sir?

386
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,260
Why is this...

387
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:48,030
This is...

388
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,630
(Is this how you use it?)

389
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:56,010
Sir, is this okay?

390
00:16:57,210 --> 00:16:58,639
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

391
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:00,809
Make sure it's locked tight. It's spraying everywhere.

392
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:02,510
- Where?
- It's open. Lock it tightly.

393
00:17:03,050 --> 00:17:04,050
Where?

394
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,680
Turn it off.

395
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:08,550
Close all of it. That's right.

396
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:10,850
Isn't it refreshing?

397
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:14,160
(The proper tick treatment finally starts.)

398
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,960
It's him.

399
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:17,830
Snow.

400
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:19,930
(Next up is John Snow who already dominated Kwang Soo.)

401
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:22,630
(He still needs to be treated.)

402
00:17:23,330 --> 00:17:24,330
(Turning away)

403
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:26,900
(Turning away)

404
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:30,240
(When Kwang Soo gets closer, Snow takes a step away.)

405
00:17:32,210 --> 00:17:35,110
(After finally grabbing the rope, Kwang Soo tries to spray on him.)

406
00:17:36,650 --> 00:17:38,950
(He seems annoyed by Kwang Soo.)

407
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:42,020
(Snow shoos him away.)

408
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:44,250
(Sighing)

409
00:17:44,550 --> 00:17:46,719
I think Snow is holding a grudge against you.

410
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:49,230
I don't know. Why does he hate me so much?

411
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:51,830
He treats me like I'm his parents' enemy.

412
00:17:53,330 --> 00:17:54,459
While he was grazing,

413
00:17:54,460 --> 00:17:56,230
I tried to treat him carefully. And then...

414
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:58,200
(Turning serious)

415
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:02,670
When I saw him do that, I stopped myself.

416
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:06,080
He went back to grazing, so I approached him again to spray.

417
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:07,580
(Turning serious for the 2nd time)

418
00:18:08,950 --> 00:18:10,210
Then he walked away.

419
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:14,480
So I told my senior about it.

420
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,119
When he held the rope, Snow remained still.

421
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,190
But when I did it,

422
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:19,190
he overpowered me with strength.

423
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:22,059
Have you heard them eating?

424
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:23,060
Isn't it wonderful?

425
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:25,259
Don't they seem to really enjoy it?

426
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:26,260
(After their work, they take a moment to watch the horses graze.)

427
00:18:26,261 --> 00:18:27,560
It's totally ASMR.

428
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:30,099
You know how UFC fighters eat...

429
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:33,369
like crazy after an intense match?

430
00:18:33,370 --> 00:18:34,700
It must be similar for them.

431
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:36,509
After running a marathon...

432
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:37,810
(Morris' eating grass ASMR)

433
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:42,650
(Back from her adventure, Yeonjin also enjoys the grass.)

434
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:47,120
(John Snow who protected the pasture by himself remains dignified.)

435
00:18:50,450 --> 00:18:53,620
(This aggressive and unrefined chewing)

436
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:59,630
(King Arthur eats more simply because he's bigger.)

437
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,000
They eat endlessly.

438
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:05,070
They just eat, sleep, and poop.

439
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:07,400
How many times do our horses poop in a day?

440
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:08,910
Six times.

441
00:19:09,210 --> 00:19:10,670
- What do you think, Kwang Soo?
- Twelve times.

442
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:12,910
They poop 23 times.

443
00:19:14,710 --> 00:19:16,479
(After learning a horse fact that they didn't need to know,)

444
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:18,250
(the trainees finish their first day's work.)

445
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:22,590
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

446
00:19:23,650 --> 00:19:26,290
(The trainees come here to eat dinner.)

447
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:27,819
Hello.

448
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:28,859
Welcome.

449
00:19:28,860 --> 00:19:30,230
- Hello.
- Hello.

450
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:33,429
One kalguksu, one ramyeon,

451
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:34,729
and one grilled tilefish, please.

452
00:19:34,730 --> 00:19:35,969
- Grilled tilefish?
- Yes.

453
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:37,569
Is it the same as what's written on the menu?

454
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:38,570
That's right.

455
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,270
What did we do today?

456
00:19:42,410 --> 00:19:43,469
What did we do today?

457
00:19:43,470 --> 00:19:44,539
We cleaned up poop and...

458
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:47,580
We took out the horses,

459
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:49,010
and they ran away.

460
00:19:50,810 --> 00:19:52,750
This is what I wanted to do.

461
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,349
Let's say that this is a horse.

462
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:56,789
The CEO walks one step ahead of him.

463
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:58,720
- My horse kept walking ahead of me.
- Right.

464
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:02,029
When there's something he wants to eat, he pulls like this.

465
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:04,460
Then I get pulled all of a sudden.

466
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:08,669
I kept blocking the way to show my back to the horse.

467
00:20:08,670 --> 00:20:09,729
With his head...

468
00:20:09,730 --> 00:20:11,099
- Doesn't he push you?
- While I was walking...

469
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,139
Doesn't he push you?

470
00:20:12,140 --> 00:20:13,140
It was the same for me.

471
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,510
He bumped into my shoulder intentionally.

472
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:19,540
Tomorrow, I need to establish dominance first.

473
00:20:20,110 --> 00:20:22,949
It's already too late for me with Snow.

474
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,350
(Laughing)

475
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:25,450
What about Yeonjin?

476
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,419
- Is it the same with Yeonjin?
- Yeonjin...

477
00:20:27,420 --> 00:20:29,820
No, I can control Yeonjin.

478
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:31,750
When I tsk,

479
00:20:32,290 --> 00:20:34,320
she seems to listen to me.

480
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:37,630
But Snow... Horses also do this.

481
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:42,200
They really do it. I'm serious.

482
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,729
When I sprayed him,

483
00:20:43,730 --> 00:20:45,300
he was eating grass and then...

484
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:50,140
(Kwang Soo had a hard time bonding with his horse.)

485
00:20:50,610 --> 00:20:52,879
Here's your seafood ramyeon.

486
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:55,379
This is real seafood ramyeon.

487
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:57,350
It can't be bad with mussels in it.

488
00:20:57,950 --> 00:21:00,079
I haven't eaten top shell kalguksu in a long time.

489
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:01,380
(Seafood ramyeon and top shell kalguksu are served.)

490
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,690
These aren't ordinary noodles either.

491
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:05,959
What kind of noodles are these?

492
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:07,319
They're fresh noodles made with hijiki.

493
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,390
- Fresh noodles made with hijiki?
- Hijiki?

494
00:21:10,490 --> 00:21:13,830
(Trying a sip of kalguksu broth made with hijiki noodles)

495
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,200
Gosh, it's good.

496
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:18,000
It tastes like seaweed soup that's very rich.

497
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,770
- Enjoy your food.
- You too.

498
00:21:28,180 --> 00:21:29,410
It's really good.

499
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:31,580
(Slurping)

500
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:41,559
(A rush of hot, refreshing soup)

501
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,490
(Next is seafood ramyeon.)

502
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,170
Which ramyeon brand is this?

503
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:53,540
I don't know.

504
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:56,870
- How are the noodles this chewy?
- I know.

505
00:21:57,410 --> 00:21:59,039
Sir, which ramyeon brand is this?

506
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,679
- What?
- Which ramyeon brand is it?

507
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:03,209
The ramyeon noodles are...

508
00:22:03,210 --> 00:22:04,309
Then...

509
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:05,649
The sauce is different.

510
00:22:05,650 --> 00:22:07,050
We make it ourselves.

511
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:08,849
(I see.)

512
00:22:08,850 --> 00:22:11,350
- That's why it tastes totally new.
- You're right.

513
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:13,660
No, it's super delicious.

514
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:15,789
It's something I've never tasted before.

515
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:17,490
(Before they're over the taste of seafood ramyeon)

516
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:20,929
- This is grilled tilefish.
- This is grilled tilefish. And...

517
00:22:20,930 --> 00:22:21,930
(Grilled tilefish shows itself.)

518
00:22:22,730 --> 00:22:24,400
(Crispy outside, soft inside)

519
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,500
(Kyung Soo is amazed.)

520
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:32,840
(Kyung Soo is impressed.)

521
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:38,880
This is so good. This is the best dish.

522
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:42,150
It's just like fried chicken.

523
00:22:44,690 --> 00:22:48,690
(Relentless tilefish killer...)

524
00:22:52,260 --> 00:22:57,830
(and the noodle killer with perfect strength control)

525
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:05,780
(Wolfing it down without looking up)

526
00:23:06,580 --> 00:23:08,779
(Their meal finished in an instant just like that.)

527
00:23:08,780 --> 00:23:09,879
Right.

528
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:11,280
Can you post it now?

529
00:23:11,850 --> 00:23:14,550
(They want to sell horse manure compost on a thrifting app.)

530
00:23:15,490 --> 00:23:18,089
(Kyung Soo is surprised.)

531
00:23:18,090 --> 00:23:20,590
Someone posted three hours ago to give away horse dung.

532
00:23:20,790 --> 00:23:22,559
"Giving away horse dung for manure usage."

533
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:23,560
(Kyung Soo starts market research to sell the compost.)

534
00:23:23,561 --> 00:23:24,790
There was a post one day ago too.

535
00:23:24,990 --> 00:23:26,799
"I can proudly say it's top-tier soft soil..."

536
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:28,730
"free of stones."

537
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:32,940
Their horse dung is in pretty good condition.

538
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:34,300
It's round.

539
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:36,669
You're right.

540
00:23:36,670 --> 00:23:37,740
(The compost market is unexpectedly crowded.)

541
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:39,009
"Top notch?"

542
00:23:39,010 --> 00:23:40,410
(They try to come up with the title.)

543
00:23:40,740 --> 00:23:42,580
- "Top notch..." - "Top quality."

544
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:44,780
How does "top quality, premium" sound?

545
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,649
"I can proudly say it's top quality, premium soil."

546
00:23:47,650 --> 00:23:48,680
Let us use "proudly" too.

547
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,220
"I swear it's top quality soil."

548
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:56,259
(He even went as far as to swear.)

549
00:23:56,260 --> 00:23:58,530
"I swear it's top quality, premium soil?"

550
00:23:59,430 --> 00:24:00,730
It makes it sound more trustworthy.

551
00:24:02,230 --> 00:24:03,230
Are you posting it now?

552
00:24:03,270 --> 00:24:04,370
No, I'll post later when I'm back at the dorm.

553
00:24:04,830 --> 00:24:07,799
(He decided to make the post when he's back at the dorm.)

554
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,869
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

555
00:24:09,870 --> 00:24:13,040
(With that, the dinner ends.)

556
00:24:15,340 --> 00:24:17,980
I keep forgetting we're in Jeju Island.

557
00:24:18,820 --> 00:24:19,850
Right?

558
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:21,750
It's warm.

559
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:25,520
(They arrive at the training camp run by the farm.)

560
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:26,790
What's this?

561
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:29,060
All three rooms have a toilet each.

562
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:31,430
(1 person per room, and there's still 1 free room.)

563
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:33,230
Shall we put our luggage in this room?

564
00:24:33,330 --> 00:24:35,400
And sleep over there?

565
00:24:35,670 --> 00:24:37,100
(Okay.)

566
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:41,200
(Out of the 3 rooms, they put their luggage in 1 room.)

567
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:45,270
(And they sleep in the same room for no reason.)

568
00:24:46,410 --> 00:24:50,410
(Kyung Soo has finished showering first.)

569
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:55,550
(He starts to eat bread.)

570
00:24:58,820 --> 00:25:01,820
(His work phone)

571
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,900
(Kyung Soo is checking something.)

572
00:25:09,070 --> 00:25:11,000
(Mouth twitching)

573
00:25:12,030 --> 00:25:13,999
(Kyung Soo laughs.)

574
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,870
(Kyung Soo laughs as he watches something.)

575
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,040
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

576
00:25:19,940 --> 00:25:21,210
I found something...

577
00:25:22,010 --> 00:25:23,510
- very funny.
- What is it?

578
00:25:25,780 --> 00:25:28,420
- The CEO's ID is...
- Yes.

579
00:25:29,420 --> 00:25:30,420
"Bushman."

580
00:25:30,790 --> 00:25:32,389
(Kyung Soo found the account of the farm's CEO.)

581
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:34,820
And you can see...

582
00:25:35,260 --> 00:25:37,660
all the past sales posts here.

583
00:25:37,930 --> 00:25:40,500
What he wrote is so funny.

584
00:25:40,860 --> 00:25:42,600
It's a tractor bucket.

585
00:25:43,870 --> 00:25:44,969
(Packed with text)

586
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:47,140
He's talkative even on the thrifting app.

587
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:50,210
"This bucket was so good to me."

588
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:53,780
"It helped me clear away stones."

589
00:25:53,940 --> 00:25:55,980
- Why did he...
- He wrote the full story.

590
00:25:56,710 --> 00:25:58,919
(Next item: A camper solar battery)

591
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:00,919
"I wanted to make a camper, but I lost interest,"

592
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,980
"so I'm selling it cheaply."

593
00:26:02,650 --> 00:26:06,020
He must include his story in the posts.

594
00:26:06,690 --> 00:26:08,590
He uses this app so frequently.

595
00:26:09,130 --> 00:26:11,889
(Next item: A wood burner)

596
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:13,099
"It can produce fire..."

597
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:14,499
- "strong enough to make..." - "strong enough to make..."

598
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:15,630
- "a sauna." - "a sauna."

599
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,669
(He exaggerates a bit too.)

600
00:26:18,670 --> 00:26:19,840
Firewood too.

601
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:22,810
"Well-dried, high quality cypress."

602
00:26:22,940 --> 00:26:23,940
At the end, he wrote,

603
00:26:24,570 --> 00:26:26,479
"Contact the woodcutter."

604
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,509
(Contact the woodcutter.)

605
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:28,580
This is so funny.

606
00:26:28,910 --> 00:26:31,550
(The CEO has a way with humor.)

607
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:33,919
Quite a lot of people viewed his posts.

608
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,250
They're all sold.

609
00:26:35,890 --> 00:26:38,249
He managed to give away and sell all his items.

610
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:40,790
- He's a thrifting app addict.
- He's an addict.

611
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:44,290
Mr. Sung Joon's ID is...

612
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:45,830
"Fighting Panda."

613
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,759
What's this? It's him?

614
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:49,829
"Fighting Panda."

615
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:51,729
(Kyung Soo found Mr. Sung Joon's account too.)

616
00:26:51,730 --> 00:26:53,240
But he's such a quiet person.

617
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:56,069
(Fiddling)

618
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:57,470
- Are you going to text him?
- What?

619
00:26:57,910 --> 00:26:58,940
No.

620
00:26:59,010 --> 00:27:00,110
Do it.

621
00:27:02,410 --> 00:27:04,610
Send, "Are you open for a negotiation?"

622
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,579
"Sell it for five dollars."

623
00:27:07,580 --> 00:27:08,580
(They finished going through the farm people's accounts.)

624
00:27:08,581 --> 00:27:09,820
"Could we negotiate?"

625
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:13,420
Post it now.

626
00:27:13,990 --> 00:27:15,020
- What?
- Post it.

627
00:27:15,730 --> 00:27:18,060
(They'll write the sales post for the horse manure compost now.)

628
00:27:18,390 --> 00:27:19,629
What should our nickname be?

629
00:27:19,630 --> 00:27:21,160
(1. Decide the ID.)

630
00:27:21,430 --> 00:27:22,430
Something...

631
00:27:23,130 --> 00:27:24,230
friendly, like this?

632
00:27:25,740 --> 00:27:27,270
- It's a trustworthy name, right?
- Yes.

633
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:29,640
"Yeonjin's Dad."

634
00:27:30,310 --> 00:27:32,240
You wouldn't lie with this kind of nickname.

635
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,680
What should the first photo be? The main photo.

636
00:27:34,810 --> 00:27:36,979
- This?
- Isn't this the best photo?

637
00:27:36,980 --> 00:27:38,150
Yes.

638
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:42,490
Let's add the photos posted by Fighting Panda to ours.

639
00:27:42,620 --> 00:27:43,720
Sure.

640
00:27:44,950 --> 00:27:47,319
This, this...

641
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:48,320
(They borrow Fighting Panda's photos.)

642
00:27:48,321 --> 00:27:49,490
You chose this.

643
00:27:50,830 --> 00:27:51,890
The title.

644
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:55,300
(3. Decide the title of the sales post.)

645
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:58,470
Let's make the title simple.

646
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:01,370
"Top quality, premium..."

647
00:28:02,610 --> 00:28:04,210
- "potting mix..." - "Selling?"

648
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:06,540
"Selling."

649
00:28:07,580 --> 00:28:08,940
- "Selling?" - "Selling."

650
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:13,350
(They kept the title simple.)

651
00:28:13,450 --> 00:28:14,450
(4. Write the content of the post.)

652
00:28:14,451 --> 00:28:17,489
"Very good potting mix."

653
00:28:17,490 --> 00:28:19,159
Something potting mix would sound nice.

654
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:20,589
"Very good..."

655
00:28:20,590 --> 00:28:22,790
(Trying to think of a good tag line)

656
00:28:23,330 --> 00:28:25,230
"It's like wild ginseng for plants."

657
00:28:25,730 --> 00:28:27,530
(Kyung Soo laughs.)

658
00:28:27,830 --> 00:28:28,930
"A nutrient bomb?"

659
00:28:29,630 --> 00:28:31,030
"Bomb" sounds a bit...

660
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:36,010
What about "fermented organic matter?"

661
00:28:36,110 --> 00:28:38,609
(Kyung Soo laughs.)

662
00:28:38,610 --> 00:28:40,010
It sounds like I should eat it.

663
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:42,379
(The trainees are stuck on the first line.)

664
00:28:42,380 --> 00:28:43,750
Let's think about it.

665
00:28:44,380 --> 00:28:45,980
AI can write it for you.

666
00:28:47,350 --> 00:28:49,319
I asked AI to write a prompt.

667
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:50,449
(In the end, they borrow the power of AI.)

668
00:28:50,450 --> 00:28:51,750
Tell me if you find anything good.

669
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:53,859
"It reduces the chance of failure for a novice,"

670
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:55,620
"and it increases the quality for the experienced."

671
00:28:55,930 --> 00:28:58,359
"Time will prove the unseen difference." Sounds good.

672
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,760
We should use it.

673
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:01,730
It makes me want to buy the product.

674
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,069
You must buy it.

675
00:29:03,070 --> 00:29:05,329
I'll definitely buy this.

676
00:29:05,330 --> 00:29:06,840
(The AI gave pretty good lines.)

677
00:29:07,470 --> 00:29:10,339
(Kwang Soo is writing something enthusiastically.)

678
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:11,340
What about this?

679
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:13,379
"Special note."

680
00:29:13,380 --> 00:29:15,580
"The potting mix made an appearance on 'Jack and The Beanstalk.'"

681
00:29:16,410 --> 00:29:19,250
(This time, they take a creative approach.)

682
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:20,849
Isn't it pronounced "Jack?"

683
00:29:20,850 --> 00:29:23,990
- It was "Jaeku" for me.
- Really?

684
00:29:25,420 --> 00:29:27,119
"What grew the gigantic beanstalk..."

685
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:30,290
"weren't the magic beans. It was this potting mix."

686
00:29:30,530 --> 00:29:33,629
(It wrote a movie scenario instead of a story for the post.)

687
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:36,770
Those who read this post will think...

688
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:39,840
we're some weird people.

689
00:29:40,540 --> 00:29:44,169
(Laughing)

690
00:29:44,170 --> 00:29:45,470
Jack and the beanstalks...

691
00:29:46,210 --> 00:29:47,210
Then...

692
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:50,949
Jack goes up to the sky riding on the beanstalks.

693
00:29:50,950 --> 00:29:51,950
Exactly.

694
00:29:51,951 --> 00:29:54,149
Weren't the beans magical in the original story?

695
00:29:54,150 --> 00:29:55,180
But either way,

696
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,520
- there must've been some soil.
- Because of the image it has.

697
00:29:57,590 --> 00:30:02,019
They used this potting mix for the bean.

698
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:03,129
That's how it got so big.

699
00:30:03,130 --> 00:30:04,490
(The story goes that the potting mix made the magic bean grow.)

700
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:06,600
Can I not like my own post?

701
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:09,200
Let's do this for now.

702
00:30:09,730 --> 00:30:11,499
(They finally uploaded it.)

703
00:30:11,500 --> 00:30:13,440
(They liked their own post as well.)

704
00:30:13,740 --> 00:30:14,839
Let's go to bed.

705
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:15,940
I hope people text us.

706
00:30:16,110 --> 00:30:19,240
(Hoping for a text, it's time to go to bed.)

707
00:30:20,180 --> 00:30:23,780
(When Kwang Soo lies down,)

708
00:30:25,310 --> 00:30:28,050
(Kyung Soo starts his skincare yet again.)

709
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:33,890
(He himself is ready to sleep with a facial mask on.)

710
00:30:34,590 --> 00:30:36,359
What time did we need to wake up again?

711
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,460
At 9am.

712
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:41,430
(They go to bed early for tomorrow.)

713
00:30:42,060 --> 00:30:45,300
(The night in Jeju Island full of stars pass by.)

714
00:30:51,910 --> 00:30:52,980
We got a message.

715
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:54,110
From who?

716
00:30:54,111 --> 00:30:57,810
(They got a message on the thrifting app.)

717
00:31:00,180 --> 00:31:01,550
They sent one, just the number.

718
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:03,990
Do they want one pack?

719
00:31:06,290 --> 00:31:07,420
Just number one?

720
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:10,760
Can you reply, "Hello. Would you like to purchase?"

721
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:12,859
(Although the mysterious customer disappeared after leaving "1")

722
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:15,830
- Is it too much if they buy it all?
- Yes.

723
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:22,500
(As they wait for the reply, they start today.)

724
00:31:23,670 --> 00:31:27,580
(They're having a simple breakfast before leaving.)

725
00:31:27,940 --> 00:31:31,049
To recharge yourself with protein,

726
00:31:31,050 --> 00:31:33,680
which you've used up overnight...

727
00:31:35,580 --> 00:31:37,850
(Protein)

728
00:31:38,390 --> 00:31:39,659
We should have it with ramyeon.

729
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:41,120
It tastes amazing with ramyeon.

730
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:44,260
This is most convenient.

731
00:31:44,690 --> 00:31:46,230
It has so much cheese.

732
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:50,470
(In one bite)

733
00:31:51,230 --> 00:31:53,869
(They eat a hearty meal.)

734
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:56,910
(They're ready to work today.)

735
00:31:59,340 --> 00:32:03,080
(GBRB Farm Operation-Go Go Farm)

736
00:32:03,780 --> 00:32:08,020
(Current time: 9:08am)

737
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:09,749
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning, sir.

738
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:10,819
I came late.

739
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:11,820
- Sir.
- Yes?

740
00:32:11,821 --> 00:32:13,159
I was so shocked.

741
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,219
You thought I wouldn't come?

742
00:32:14,220 --> 00:32:15,690
Right, because you didn't arrive by 9am.

743
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:18,890
Isn't this Fighting Panda?

744
00:32:19,330 --> 00:32:20,900
Yes, it's me.

745
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:22,430
Why didn't you...

746
00:32:23,130 --> 00:32:24,899
reply to our message?

747
00:32:24,900 --> 00:32:26,339
(Last night, the trainees sent a text to Sung Joon.)

748
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:27,399
You didn't reply him?

749
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:29,569
The sender asked about my nickname,

750
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:31,410
so I thought, "They must be someone strange."

751
00:32:31,910 --> 00:32:34,339
What do you mean strange?

752
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:36,309
- They could ask out of curiosity.
- That's right.

753
00:32:36,310 --> 00:32:38,779
You should tell them about that and get to know each other...

754
00:32:38,780 --> 00:32:40,279
so that you can start buying and selling...

755
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:41,419
from each other, no?

756
00:32:41,420 --> 00:32:42,420
You're right.

757
00:32:43,250 --> 00:32:46,719
We even got a message from someone.

758
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,760
I see.

759
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,659
And sorry to say this,

760
00:32:50,660 --> 00:32:52,529
but we're selling it one dollar cheaper than you.

761
00:32:52,530 --> 00:32:53,530
I see.

762
00:32:53,531 --> 00:32:54,759
(Laughing)

763
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:56,329
- I'm sorry.
- I see.

764
00:32:56,330 --> 00:32:58,029
Please understand.

765
00:32:58,030 --> 00:33:00,100
- Okay.
- We're in a rush.

766
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:02,470
Is this the place?

767
00:33:03,370 --> 00:33:05,469
- Yes. It's very near, isn't it?
- Yes.

768
00:33:05,470 --> 00:33:06,780
(They came to draw fresh underground water for the horses.)

769
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:08,940
One should get on it.

770
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:12,210
(Kwang Soo sets an example by getting on it first.)

771
00:33:12,780 --> 00:33:14,680
Put this inside.

772
00:33:16,420 --> 00:33:17,789
Put it all the way inside and hold it tight.

773
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:19,459
- Okay.
- Will it come out strong?

774
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:22,119
Kyung Soo, push it down at once.

775
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,159
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

776
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:24,160
Hold it tight.

777
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:28,760
(Leaking)

778
00:33:30,300 --> 00:33:31,800
It leaks!

779
00:33:33,170 --> 00:33:34,399
(Turning on the lever suddenly)

780
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,770
What do I do with this?

781
00:33:36,910 --> 00:33:37,910
(A morning water show)

782
00:33:37,911 --> 00:33:40,639
- This...
- You need to hold it properly.

783
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:42,080
How can I hold this properly?

784
00:33:43,110 --> 00:33:44,680
- Kwang Soo.
- This...

785
00:33:45,380 --> 00:33:46,549
Something's wrong with it!

786
00:33:46,550 --> 00:33:48,420
The water is going in fine.

787
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:49,520
Sorry?

788
00:33:50,503 --> 00:33:51,490
Did this happen yesterday?

789
00:33:51,890 --> 00:33:53,089
Yes, it happened yesterday too.

790
00:33:53,090 --> 00:33:54,959
- You should've told me!
- You should've said so.

791
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:57,530
(He is cheerfully careless.)

792
00:33:58,030 --> 00:33:59,330
- Is it enough?
- Yes.

793
00:33:59,460 --> 00:34:02,030
(The water show ends once the water tank is filled up.)

794
00:34:03,030 --> 00:34:06,600
(Now, they head to the farm.)

795
00:34:07,370 --> 00:34:09,439
(It rains on their way to work.)

796
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,310
It has a nice atmosphere with the rain.

797
00:34:12,370 --> 00:34:13,840
You're feeding them today, right?

798
00:34:14,140 --> 00:34:16,849
Some horses are pregnant, so we'll give them a special meal.

799
00:34:16,850 --> 00:34:17,850
(They'll be giving pregnant horses breakfast.)

800
00:34:17,851 --> 00:34:18,950
Was it Grace?

801
00:34:19,550 --> 00:34:20,950
- Jacy?
- Jacy.

802
00:34:24,620 --> 00:34:27,990
(They've arrived at the farm.)

803
00:34:28,820 --> 00:34:31,130
(The farm's morning is moist with rain.)

804
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:34,360
(The horses should be feeling hungry around this time.)

805
00:34:35,100 --> 00:34:38,300
(Horses become sensitive when they're about to give birth,)

806
00:34:39,070 --> 00:34:42,600
(so they're gathered in one range for better management.)

807
00:34:43,310 --> 00:34:46,639
(They're going to be feeding those pregnant horses first.)

808
00:34:46,640 --> 00:34:47,640
(Morning Task Schedule)

809
00:34:47,641 --> 00:34:49,810
(Feed pregnant horses)

810
00:34:50,410 --> 00:34:52,380
Horses don't move about much because it's raining.

811
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:53,719
- Sorry?
- Horses don't move about much...

812
00:34:53,720 --> 00:34:54,720
because it's raining.

813
00:34:54,721 --> 00:34:57,689
No, they're taking shelter under the bamboo trees.

814
00:34:57,690 --> 00:34:59,489
They're taking shelter from the rain?

815
00:34:59,490 --> 00:35:00,860
(They're taking shelter from the rain under the trees.)

816
00:35:00,983 --> 00:35:03,153
They look so cute taking shelter.

817
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:07,130
(To give the horses water,)

818
00:35:08,430 --> 00:35:10,800
(he starts to wash the water bucket.)

819
00:35:11,696 --> 00:35:13,866
Sung Joon, is she the elderly lady who picks bracken?

820
00:35:15,140 --> 00:35:20,110
(Someone walks slowly toward the farm.)

821
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:24,580
(She walks closer while looking around.)

822
00:35:25,050 --> 00:35:27,250
- Who is she?
- She's a staff member.

823
00:35:27,809 --> 00:35:29,479
She isn't one of us.

824
00:35:29,620 --> 00:35:30,820
- She isn't?
- No.

825
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,790
- Excuse me.
- I'm sorry,

826
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:37,729
but this is a private property,

827
00:35:37,730 --> 00:35:38,860
and we raise horses here.

828
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,999
You can't pick bracken here. Please leave.

829
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,059
She came to pick bracken.

830
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:43,129
She came to pick bracken.

831
00:35:43,130 --> 00:35:44,130
From the neighbor.

832
00:35:44,730 --> 00:35:45,930
- One, two, three.
- Two, three.

833
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:47,600
- Bracken...
- I came...

834
00:35:47,601 --> 00:35:48,669
because I heard I could.

835
00:35:48,670 --> 00:35:50,340
- You heard you could?
- Yes.

836
00:35:50,610 --> 00:35:52,339
I'll pick until there.

837
00:35:52,340 --> 00:35:53,479
But here...

838
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:54,480
Let me pick just a bit.

839
00:35:54,481 --> 00:35:55,709
Who would pick bracken here?

840
00:35:55,710 --> 00:35:57,580
Goodness. But what is bracken?

841
00:35:58,310 --> 00:35:59,379
What's bracken?

842
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:00,880
- What's bracken?
- Yes.

843
00:36:01,505 --> 00:36:03,020
- This is bracken.
- This?

844
00:36:03,820 --> 00:36:06,219
You picked one for me when you said I couldn't.

845
00:36:06,220 --> 00:36:08,660
This is straightened bracken.

846
00:36:09,260 --> 00:36:11,089
- This is bracken.
- What are you doing?

847
00:36:11,090 --> 00:36:12,359
- Sorry?
- What are you doing?

848
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:14,299
But we're filming now.

849
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:16,800
You need to leave.

850
00:36:17,070 --> 00:36:18,070
Wait.

851
00:36:18,930 --> 00:36:19,940
We're filming.

852
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:22,240
Left foot.

853
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:23,240
- Let's put it down.
- She's filming us.

854
00:36:23,241 --> 00:36:24,740
Put it down first. One, two, three.

855
00:36:25,170 --> 00:36:26,310
Let me.

856
00:36:26,380 --> 00:36:28,039
- We're filming.
- It's okay.

857
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,209
Please go out that way.

858
00:36:29,210 --> 00:36:30,210
She's not a grandma.

859
00:36:31,150 --> 00:36:32,209
- Let's put it down.
- She's filming us.

860
00:36:32,210 --> 00:36:33,580
Put it down first. One, two, three.

861
00:36:34,021 --> 00:36:35,151
Let me.

862
00:36:35,250 --> 00:36:36,919
- We're filming.
- It's okay.

863
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:37,949
Please go out that way.

864
00:36:37,950 --> 00:36:38,950
She's not a grandma.

865
00:36:38,951 --> 00:36:40,259
- This way?
- She's not a grandma.

866
00:36:40,260 --> 00:36:42,490
What are you talking about? I'm their owner.

867
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:44,160
- You're their owner?
- Yes.

868
00:36:44,990 --> 00:36:47,160
Ma'am, you scared the foal.

869
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:49,900
Let's go!

870
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,200
Let's go!

871
00:36:52,470 --> 00:36:54,600
It's not following me because of you. Go away.

872
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:56,410
Let's go.

873
00:36:59,519 --> 00:37:01,089
Let's go!

874
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:03,610
(Feeling suspicious, Kyung Soo approaches her.)

875
00:37:03,903 --> 00:37:05,273
Why are you filming me?

876
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:08,120
Strange...

877
00:37:08,620 --> 00:37:10,390
(On guard)

878
00:37:10,690 --> 00:37:11,819
You're a celebrity.

879
00:37:11,820 --> 00:37:13,720
(She suddenly approaches the trainees.)

880
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:16,090
(Laughing)

881
00:37:16,802 --> 00:37:18,142
(Kyung Soo shouts in annoyance.)

882
00:37:19,900 --> 00:37:22,629
(The unknown bracken grandma is...)

883
00:37:22,630 --> 00:37:23,969
- Hello.
- Ye Eun.

884
00:37:23,970 --> 00:37:24,970
Yes?

885
00:37:24,971 --> 00:37:26,840
(Intern Shin Ye Eun)

886
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:28,840
(30 minutes ago)

887
00:37:28,841 --> 00:37:30,510
Isn't that an ATV?

888
00:37:31,570 --> 00:37:32,610
Do I get to ride that?

889
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:34,940
I came dressed very politely.

890
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:38,810
(As expected of the show's intern, she came dressed politely.)

891
00:37:39,010 --> 00:37:41,549
Where are the CEO and the director?

892
00:37:41,550 --> 00:37:42,550
What are they doing?

893
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:45,819
This whole situation is so funny.

894
00:37:45,820 --> 00:37:46,820
(The thought of making a secret entrance makes her laugh.)

895
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,560
I'll go and transform.

896
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:51,690
(After transforming into a farm outfit, she's on standby.)

897
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:52,859
- Do I get out?
- Yes.

898
00:37:52,860 --> 00:37:55,460
(The seniors seem to have arrived.)

899
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:58,330
I'm bad at holding back my laugh.

900
00:37:59,670 --> 00:38:01,470
(What's your outfit concept?)

901
00:38:01,570 --> 00:38:03,540
A Jeju neighbor...

902
00:38:03,870 --> 00:38:05,640
who came to pick bracken.

903
00:38:05,740 --> 00:38:08,480
I'm walking like a local here.

904
00:38:10,380 --> 00:38:11,979
You shouldn't be filming me, right?

905
00:38:11,980 --> 00:38:14,020
(That's how the bracken grandma... No,)

906
00:38:14,550 --> 00:38:15,819
(the intern joined them.)

907
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,820
Yes.

908
00:38:18,850 --> 00:38:21,190
- Do you know her?
- Yes.

909
00:38:21,460 --> 00:38:23,159
She's our intern for today.

910
00:38:23,160 --> 00:38:24,890
So he wasn't acting.

911
00:38:25,860 --> 00:38:27,260
When did you come? In the morning?

912
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,360
Yes.

913
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:30,370
Hello.

914
00:38:31,600 --> 00:38:33,140
You did pick bracken.

915
00:38:33,970 --> 00:38:35,439
- He...
- You really picked it?

916
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:37,570
He told me to leave.

917
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:40,080
So I asked, "What's bracken?" And he picked one for me.

918
00:38:40,710 --> 00:38:42,909
- "This is bracken." - You're so nice.

919
00:38:42,910 --> 00:38:44,109
You don't act like it, but you're kind.

920
00:38:44,110 --> 00:38:45,579
(He's the type to quietly treat you nicely.)

921
00:38:45,580 --> 00:38:47,180
- Bracken.
- Let's go and work.

922
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,380
Okay.

923
00:38:49,550 --> 00:38:51,519
(They get ready to feed the horses.)

924
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:52,750
You didn't know I was coming, did you?

925
00:38:52,850 --> 00:38:54,019
Not at all. How could I have known?

926
00:38:54,020 --> 00:38:55,819
What did you think when I was making a fuss there?

927
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:56,890
Did you think it was me?

928
00:38:56,990 --> 00:38:58,259
I didn't. How could I?

929
00:38:58,260 --> 00:38:59,730
I just thought you were some strange lady.

930
00:39:00,500 --> 00:39:01,599
Everyone, look here.

931
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:02,600
Carrots.

932
00:39:03,270 --> 00:39:04,369
I was going to get to work in the morning,

933
00:39:04,370 --> 00:39:06,570
and someone left a box of carrots at the entrance.

934
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:09,039
They just leave things there without telling you?

935
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:11,610
Yes. These are Jeju carrots.

936
00:39:12,570 --> 00:39:14,209
The ugly ones which they can't sell?

937
00:39:14,210 --> 00:39:15,809
But they're still as tasty.

938
00:39:15,810 --> 00:39:17,110
The villagers...

939
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:20,420
sometimes bring a pile of sweet potato stems.

940
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:23,350
Everyone around here does good deeds very quietly.

941
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:26,560
They just leave it there without leaving a single text.

942
00:39:27,620 --> 00:39:30,330
We made a post on the thrifting app.

943
00:39:30,430 --> 00:39:31,559
Without saying anything,

944
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:33,360
they just sent number one.

945
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:34,460
To buy one?

946
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:35,829
I don't know about that.

947
00:39:35,830 --> 00:39:37,500
Does it mean they want to buy one?

948
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,529
They wouldn't have sent to the wrong person.

949
00:39:39,530 --> 00:39:41,499
Or it might be that.

950
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:43,039
The number game. You need to text back two.

951
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:45,010
Why would they play the number game with me?

952
00:39:45,140 --> 00:39:46,169
(At a loss for words)

953
00:39:46,170 --> 00:39:48,080
- Why would they suddenly...
- Since they texted one.

954
00:39:48,810 --> 00:39:50,150
Shall I text back two?

955
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:52,149
That sounds fun.

956
00:39:52,150 --> 00:39:54,850
What we should know is, thrifting is about mind games.

957
00:39:55,220 --> 00:39:58,019
When they ask you something, just say yes.

958
00:39:58,020 --> 00:39:59,419
(Just say "yes" and nothing else.)

959
00:39:59,420 --> 00:40:01,120
They're the ones who need the item.

960
00:40:01,220 --> 00:40:02,990
If we act like we're desperate to sell,

961
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,389
- they...
- But sir.

962
00:40:04,390 --> 00:40:06,230
You say to keep the conversation simple,

963
00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:09,030
but I saw all the posts you've made so far.

964
00:40:09,300 --> 00:40:11,729
You wrote all your long and winding stories.

965
00:40:11,730 --> 00:40:13,900
- You saw that?
- I read everything.

966
00:40:14,740 --> 00:40:18,710
I thought they were written by a middle school student.

967
00:40:19,370 --> 00:40:21,140
That motorcycle is...

968
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:22,639
I got caught.

969
00:40:22,640 --> 00:40:23,979
You counterattacked and...

970
00:40:23,980 --> 00:40:25,950
(One long story for each item)

971
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:27,979
He has so much to say on the post.

972
00:40:27,980 --> 00:40:29,649
You could've just kept it simple...

973
00:40:29,650 --> 00:40:31,249
and posted the item and the price.

974
00:40:31,250 --> 00:40:32,250
You're right.

975
00:40:32,420 --> 00:40:34,889
- You wrote all the stories.
- The ID is "Bushman."

976
00:40:34,890 --> 00:40:35,919
- You were...
- Here.

977
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:37,289
"It left me with a shameful memory when I was young."

978
00:40:37,290 --> 00:40:39,859
"It was stuck in the warehouse for long because I was upset,"

979
00:40:39,860 --> 00:40:40,930
- "and I'm releasing it now." - TMI.

980
00:40:41,030 --> 00:40:42,760
- On the post...
- Yes, speaking.

981
00:40:43,730 --> 00:40:46,269
What's with the phone call? Is this real?

982
00:40:46,270 --> 00:40:47,599
(Now, even the phone call is suspicious.)

983
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:50,469
I saw your post on the thrifting app.

984
00:40:50,470 --> 00:40:51,640
Yes.

985
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,379
Where should I go to?

986
00:40:53,380 --> 00:40:55,339
- It's a farm.
- The caller speaks in Jeju dialect.

987
00:40:55,340 --> 00:40:56,510
Is it that farm?

988
00:40:56,980 --> 00:41:00,349
Let me see. That farm is...

989
00:41:00,350 --> 00:41:01,749
- He's a Jeju resident.
- A real Jeju resident.

990
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:02,880
That's a very thick Jeju dialect.

991
00:41:05,650 --> 00:41:06,660
What does that mean?

992
00:41:07,020 --> 00:41:10,029
(The trainees can't understand.)

993
00:41:10,030 --> 00:41:11,789
I'll leave when you give me a call.

994
00:41:11,790 --> 00:41:13,659
What time should I get there?

995
00:41:13,660 --> 00:41:16,599
- I'll call back in 30 minutes.
- From what I see...

996
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:17,870
- Thank you.
- I think...

997
00:41:18,170 --> 00:41:20,139
He must've planned all of this last night.

998
00:41:20,140 --> 00:41:21,639
It's hard to believe.

999
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:23,269
He must've asked one of his friends...

1000
00:41:23,270 --> 00:41:25,910
- and planned this out.
- No, look.

1001
00:41:26,170 --> 00:41:28,139
"May I come and pick it up myself? Of course."

1002
00:41:28,140 --> 00:41:30,350
The customer isn't using a dialect here.

1003
00:41:30,750 --> 00:41:33,450
But out of the blue, he's using an incomprehensible...

1004
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:36,280
- "Can I?" - "I will."

1005
00:41:36,620 --> 00:41:37,789
Shall we go give out the carrots?

1006
00:41:37,790 --> 00:41:38,849
Not just the carrots. Hold on.

1007
00:41:38,850 --> 00:41:39,890
- Let's open this door.
- Is it in there?

1008
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:43,020
(The feed shed is open.)

1009
00:41:43,290 --> 00:41:45,729
One bag that has "Korean oats" on it.

1010
00:41:45,730 --> 00:41:47,900
(Transferring the oats and feed first)

1011
00:41:48,530 --> 00:41:50,599
(Kwang Soo tries to move the carrot box.)

1012
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,770
Get over there, Ye Eun.

1013
00:41:51,930 --> 00:41:53,000
- Okay!
- What...

1014
00:41:53,640 --> 00:41:54,640
Ye Eun.

1015
00:41:55,170 --> 00:41:56,170
No, it's okay.

1016
00:41:56,171 --> 00:41:57,870
Gosh, Ye Eun.

1017
00:41:58,740 --> 00:42:00,579
Ye Eun, can you pass this over?

1018
00:42:00,580 --> 00:42:02,709
(Grabbing)

1019
00:42:02,710 --> 00:42:04,410
(Impressed)

1020
00:42:04,910 --> 00:42:06,110
Isn't it heavy?

1021
00:42:06,380 --> 00:42:07,880
- Yes, it is.
- Be careful.

1022
00:42:08,650 --> 00:42:11,020
(And the last special ingredient)

1023
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:12,289
- Is it salt?
- It says "salt."

1024
00:42:12,290 --> 00:42:14,090
Yes, those are mineral blocks.

1025
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:17,589
The horses lick them when they sweat.

1026
00:42:17,590 --> 00:42:19,189
They need to take in some salt.

1027
00:42:19,190 --> 00:42:20,599
- What a great idea.
- I didn't know such existed.

1028
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:21,600
These are...

1029
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:24,599
All right. Let's go into the pregnant mare zone. Come.

1030
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,600
Okay.

1031
00:42:25,730 --> 00:42:27,170
More.

1032
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:29,139
More. Please close the gate.

1033
00:42:29,140 --> 00:42:30,209
(Ranch tip: Jeju Island's grass in April is still growing,)

1034
00:42:30,210 --> 00:42:31,270
(so pregnant mares are given special feed to replenish nutrients.)

1035
00:42:32,070 --> 00:42:33,410
Try saying, "Mamama."

1036
00:42:34,110 --> 00:42:36,240
Mamama!

1037
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:39,350
Mamama!

1038
00:42:39,650 --> 00:42:40,980
Here she comes.

1039
00:42:41,550 --> 00:42:43,789
- Mamama!
- She's responding.

1040
00:42:43,790 --> 00:42:45,650
(The horses gather at Kwang Soo's call.)

1041
00:42:46,860 --> 00:42:48,820
Mamama!

1042
00:42:49,620 --> 00:42:50,930
This feels great.

1043
00:42:52,290 --> 00:42:54,700
Mamama!

1044
00:42:54,830 --> 00:42:57,370
Mamama!

1045
00:42:57,730 --> 00:42:59,400
Mamama!

1046
00:42:59,700 --> 00:43:00,700
Mama...

1047
00:43:00,970 --> 00:43:02,900
No, don't come to me.

1048
00:43:03,510 --> 00:43:04,510
Ma...

1049
00:43:05,410 --> 00:43:06,410
Ma!

1050
00:43:06,540 --> 00:43:07,540
Mama...

1051
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:09,310
Mamama.

1052
00:43:09,540 --> 00:43:10,879
Mamama.

1053
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:12,880
(Calling over the lost horse)

1054
00:43:13,650 --> 00:43:14,719
(Laughing)

1055
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:15,819
I called her over.

1056
00:43:15,820 --> 00:43:17,120
(Feeling proud)

1057
00:43:17,950 --> 00:43:19,890
(The horses that smelled the feed...)

1058
00:43:20,990 --> 00:43:22,459
(are stealing the carrots.)

1059
00:43:22,460 --> 00:43:23,460
She's eating the carrot.

1060
00:43:24,460 --> 00:43:25,790
Oh, dear.

1061
00:43:26,260 --> 00:43:27,530
They're digging into the feed.

1062
00:43:28,730 --> 00:43:31,970
(The feed is no exception.)

1063
00:43:32,670 --> 00:43:35,600
(Filling up with feed quickly before they feel hungry)

1064
00:43:36,870 --> 00:43:39,670
(Placing the hay on top)

1065
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:41,739
(The basic setup is done.)

1066
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:43,280
Hey. No.

1067
00:43:44,410 --> 00:43:45,480
You must eat together.

1068
00:43:46,550 --> 00:43:48,120
Stop scolding the others.

1069
00:43:49,050 --> 00:43:51,190
Eat together, okay? Stop scolding the others.

1070
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,189
- Eat together.
- She's blocking the others...

1071
00:43:54,190 --> 00:43:55,190
from eating.

1072
00:43:55,820 --> 00:43:57,830
- She's the boss around here.
- I see.

1073
00:43:58,330 --> 00:44:02,060
Horses never share what's good.

1074
00:44:03,630 --> 00:44:07,240
(While the horses are digging into the delicious hay)

1075
00:44:07,970 --> 00:44:09,369
Let's go hang the salt.

1076
00:44:09,370 --> 00:44:10,370
Let's go.

1077
00:44:10,371 --> 00:44:12,439
(Trainee Kyung Soo takes a mineral block.)

1078
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:15,339
Make sure to take the plastic wrap outside.

1079
00:44:15,340 --> 00:44:16,409
Got it.

1080
00:44:16,410 --> 00:44:18,210
The horses could have an upset stomach from eating it.

1081
00:44:20,450 --> 00:44:21,549
Let's go.

1082
00:44:21,550 --> 00:44:24,020
(Storing the plastic wrap in his pocket)

1083
00:44:24,820 --> 00:44:25,890
- Right here?
- Okay.

1084
00:44:26,790 --> 00:44:27,860
Hang it here,

1085
00:44:28,560 --> 00:44:31,129
and the horses will lick it.

1086
00:44:31,130 --> 00:44:33,129
(Hung up mineral blocks everywhere on the ranch for the horses)

1087
00:44:33,130 --> 00:44:34,259
(How's the intern?)

1088
00:44:34,260 --> 00:44:35,260
Our intern?

1089
00:44:35,261 --> 00:44:36,829
(How's the intern?)

1090
00:44:36,830 --> 00:44:38,100
I'm happy to see her.

1091
00:44:39,100 --> 00:44:41,100
But I've got to see how she gets on with the work.

1092
00:44:43,100 --> 00:44:44,239
She must be good at her job.

1093
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:45,540
(The senior is all about ability.)

1094
00:44:46,410 --> 00:44:48,579
(Meanwhile, the intern is getting the oats ready.)

1095
00:44:48,580 --> 00:44:49,680
I have a knack for this, don't I?

1096
00:44:50,310 --> 00:44:52,080
How does automatic distribution sound?

1097
00:44:53,150 --> 00:44:56,050
(Showing off her competency by tilting the sack)

1098
00:44:56,580 --> 00:44:58,290
I brought oats.

1099
00:45:01,990 --> 00:45:03,060
Try it.

1100
00:45:04,360 --> 00:45:06,590
Oats. Try the oats.

1101
00:45:07,530 --> 00:45:08,830
Dig... Oh, dear.

1102
00:45:09,730 --> 00:45:11,930
No, I was trying to give you oats.

1103
00:45:13,030 --> 00:45:14,069
Why are you avoiding me?

1104
00:45:14,070 --> 00:45:16,040
I'm just here to give you your food.

1105
00:45:17,140 --> 00:45:19,110
I was told...

1106
00:45:19,740 --> 00:45:22,240
not to stand close to the horse's feet at the studio.

1107
00:45:23,710 --> 00:45:25,550
(Running away)

1108
00:45:26,110 --> 00:45:27,350
- Ye Eun.
- Yes?

1109
00:45:28,450 --> 00:45:29,650
- Smell it.
- Is it poop?

1110
00:45:31,190 --> 00:45:32,219
(Shocked)

1111
00:45:32,220 --> 00:45:33,220
Why are you bringing poop with you?

1112
00:45:33,221 --> 00:45:35,660
Horse poop doesn't smell.

1113
00:45:37,990 --> 00:45:39,359
- What's wrong with you?
- Smell it.

1114
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:40,499
(Taken aback by the sudden poop offer)

1115
00:45:40,500 --> 00:45:41,859
You're going to smear it on my face, aren't you?

1116
00:45:41,860 --> 00:45:42,860
No, I won't.

1117
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,330
It's still poop.

1118
00:45:45,170 --> 00:45:46,170
It doesn't smell, does it?

1119
00:45:46,230 --> 00:45:47,339
- No.
- It smells of grass, right?

1120
00:45:47,340 --> 00:45:48,770
- Yes.
- Right?

1121
00:45:49,340 --> 00:45:51,439
The round droppings are cute.

1122
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:52,440
Right.

1123
00:45:52,441 --> 00:45:53,979
- Poops...
- Take some home.

1124
00:45:53,980 --> 00:45:55,709
- Dry them up, - She told him to take some home.

1125
00:45:55,710 --> 00:45:57,079
spray water on them,

1126
00:45:57,080 --> 00:45:58,510
and they become good fertilizer.

1127
00:45:59,110 --> 00:46:00,180
- Really?
- Yes.

1128
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,849
(Spotted the intern passing by)

1129
00:46:03,850 --> 00:46:04,850
Ye Eun.

1130
00:46:06,050 --> 00:46:07,689
You had a thing for ranch life, didn't you?

1131
00:46:07,690 --> 00:46:08,690
Ye Eun.

1132
00:46:09,460 --> 00:46:12,630
Hurry up and give oats to Jacy.

1133
00:46:13,390 --> 00:46:14,700
I've been told to give her oats.

1134
00:46:15,660 --> 00:46:17,470
(The superior's orders are endless.)

1135
00:46:18,030 --> 00:46:19,869
The intern is a junior and younger than you.

1136
00:46:19,870 --> 00:46:21,500
That's why I already feel at ease.

1137
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:23,270
I'm going to order her around.

1138
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:25,540
I finally have someone...

1139
00:46:26,310 --> 00:46:27,710
to boss around...

1140
00:46:27,910 --> 00:46:29,779
and talk to as much as I want.

1141
00:46:29,780 --> 00:46:30,780
(Excited to have a close junior)

1142
00:46:31,210 --> 00:46:32,380
Director!

1143
00:46:33,080 --> 00:46:34,080
Get over here.

1144
00:46:35,050 --> 00:46:36,050
What?

1145
00:46:37,050 --> 00:46:39,189
Wasn't that an order just now?

1146
00:46:39,190 --> 00:46:40,190
(She's one tough intern.)

1147
00:46:41,160 --> 00:46:43,660
Mamama.

1148
00:46:43,690 --> 00:46:46,389
I wonder which pitch they like...

1149
00:46:46,390 --> 00:46:47,400
when calling them.

1150
00:46:48,830 --> 00:46:51,600
(She's come to give oats to the pony family.)

1151
00:46:53,570 --> 00:46:57,170
(The pony mom digs into the oats.)

1152
00:46:58,110 --> 00:46:59,909
The baby needs to drink milk.

1153
00:46:59,910 --> 00:47:00,910
Right?

1154
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:02,909
(The pony dad has come.)

1155
00:47:02,910 --> 00:47:04,080
Is it tasty?

1156
00:47:04,580 --> 00:47:06,449
- Isn't she really enjoying it?
- Yes.

1157
00:47:06,450 --> 00:47:08,749
If you listen to them eat grass,

1158
00:47:08,750 --> 00:47:09,979
- Does it soothe you?
- you space out.

1159
00:47:09,980 --> 00:47:11,050
- Really?
- Yes.

1160
00:47:12,150 --> 00:47:15,090
(A short spacing out and soothing session)

1161
00:47:19,290 --> 00:47:20,300
Baby.

1162
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:22,230
Gofarm.

1163
00:47:23,200 --> 00:47:24,200
Gofarm...

1164
00:47:24,201 --> 00:47:25,730
(The intern has named the pony Gofarm.)

1165
00:47:26,130 --> 00:47:28,369
(What do you think about the name Gofarm?)

1166
00:47:28,370 --> 00:47:30,100
In my heart, that pony's name is Dohny.

1167
00:47:31,210 --> 00:47:32,440
Doh from Doh Kyung Soo...

1168
00:47:32,870 --> 00:47:35,540
and pony, hence Dohny.

1169
00:47:36,710 --> 00:47:39,509
Kyung Soo, keep checking if its teeth are coming in or not.

1170
00:47:39,510 --> 00:47:41,480
It needs to eat grass once it's five days old.

1171
00:47:41,880 --> 00:47:42,919
Wait.

1172
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:43,920
- What?
- Its teeth are coming out.

1173
00:47:44,190 --> 00:47:45,520
Its molar teeth are out.

1174
00:47:46,250 --> 00:47:48,890
It just bit my finger as if a puppy were teething.

1175
00:47:50,560 --> 00:47:54,060
(It's become a legit pony with teeth now.)

1176
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:56,360
The pony mom needs some too.

1177
00:47:57,430 --> 00:48:00,500
(Kyung Soo doesn't forget about the pony mom.)

1178
00:48:00,740 --> 00:48:01,740
Mom.

1179
00:48:02,300 --> 00:48:03,300
Dig in.

1180
00:48:04,540 --> 00:48:05,540
Enjoy it.

1181
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:08,539
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

1182
00:48:08,540 --> 00:48:09,940
- Take this.
- Okay.

1183
00:48:10,310 --> 00:48:12,479
Spread some out over there.

1184
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:13,480
Okay.

1185
00:48:14,220 --> 00:48:17,820
(So that the other horses have enough feed to eat,)

1186
00:48:18,690 --> 00:48:22,520
(feeding areas must be set up throughout the ranch.)

1187
00:48:24,530 --> 00:48:28,430
(Spreading out the feed as much as possible)

1188
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:31,870
(Returning with feelings of fulfillment)

1189
00:48:32,100 --> 00:48:33,400
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

1190
00:48:33,840 --> 00:48:35,199
What were you doing?

1191
00:48:35,200 --> 00:48:36,370
You told me to spread it out.

1192
00:48:36,770 --> 00:48:38,609
You should take the horses with you.

1193
00:48:38,610 --> 00:48:40,340
Who would go there to eat?

1194
00:48:41,180 --> 00:48:42,180
Is this a picture puzzle?

1195
00:48:42,181 --> 00:48:44,050
How would the horses know where it is?

1196
00:48:44,280 --> 00:48:45,680
- It...
- We need to talk, Sung Joon.

1197
00:48:46,880 --> 00:48:47,880
Listen.

1198
00:48:48,950 --> 00:48:50,690
He told me to spread it out.

1199
00:48:51,590 --> 00:48:52,590
You heard it too, right?

1200
00:48:53,150 --> 00:48:55,920
I would've taken the horses with me if he had told me to.

1201
00:48:56,490 --> 00:48:57,830
I'm from Seoul.

1202
00:48:58,390 --> 00:49:00,260
It's my first time here and doing this job.

1203
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:02,499
What do you think, Sung Joon?

1204
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:04,299
Am I wrong? What do you think?

1205
00:49:04,300 --> 00:49:05,470
- But...
- Be honest.

1206
00:49:07,700 --> 00:49:09,769
The horses don't know the spots.

1207
00:49:09,770 --> 00:49:11,910
(Birds of a feather flock together.)

1208
00:49:12,270 --> 00:49:14,310
- Achick! Let's go.
- That's it.

1209
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:16,579
Here it is.

1210
00:49:16,580 --> 00:49:18,279
Over here. Achick.

1211
00:49:18,280 --> 00:49:20,150
(Trainee Kwang Soo does his job while whining.)

1212
00:49:20,620 --> 00:49:21,620
Carrots, Jacy?

1213
00:49:22,580 --> 00:49:24,750
(Kwang Soo is here to check up on the pregnant mare Jacy.)

1214
00:49:24,890 --> 00:49:26,920
Check if there's a something like a mole around her teats.

1215
00:49:27,690 --> 00:49:29,159
Where? Where's the mole?

1216
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:30,659
Because she's pregnant,

1217
00:49:30,660 --> 00:49:32,930
- Yes?
- there's milk in here.

1218
00:49:33,460 --> 00:49:35,460
- Where?
- Right here.

1219
00:49:36,660 --> 00:49:37,899
- I see it.
- Right?

1220
00:49:37,900 --> 00:49:39,629
(A mare close to foaling develops colostrum on her teats.)

1221
00:49:39,630 --> 00:49:40,640
The right side.

1222
00:49:41,900 --> 00:49:43,200
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

1223
00:49:43,770 --> 00:49:45,610
You might have to help with the birthing.

1224
00:49:46,670 --> 00:49:47,739
She's close to foaling.

1225
00:49:47,740 --> 00:49:50,610
But for real, I can see something has popped out.

1226
00:49:53,820 --> 00:49:55,380
(Something is in here.)

1227
00:49:56,180 --> 00:49:57,949
She's going to give birth soon.

1228
00:49:57,950 --> 00:49:59,990
- Really?
- Put some oats on top.

1229
00:50:00,790 --> 00:50:01,790
Okay.

1230
00:50:01,790 --> 00:50:02,790
(A handful of oats for Jacy)

1231
00:50:02,791 --> 00:50:04,290
Make sure to dig in,

1232
00:50:04,690 --> 00:50:05,930
and give birth to a healthy baby.

1233
00:50:06,390 --> 00:50:07,400
Okay?

1234
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:11,200
Dig in, Jacy.

1235
00:50:11,330 --> 00:50:12,330
Mamama.

1236
00:50:12,330 --> 00:50:13,330
(From feed, hay, carrots, to oats)

1237
00:50:13,840 --> 00:50:16,600
(Filled with various nutrients)

1238
00:50:17,940 --> 00:50:21,980
(The special breakfast for the pregnant mares is over.)

1239
00:50:22,410 --> 00:50:24,179
(It's time to move on to the next task.)

1240
00:50:24,180 --> 00:50:27,080
You're all about to cut some fresh grass.

1241
00:50:27,880 --> 00:50:30,350
During the fallow period,

1242
00:50:30,650 --> 00:50:32,119
we were told to plant seeds,

1243
00:50:32,120 --> 00:50:33,649
and those plants have grown up to here.

1244
00:50:33,650 --> 00:50:34,859
I see.

1245
00:50:34,860 --> 00:50:35,989
You use the land while it's vacant.

1246
00:50:35,990 --> 00:50:37,729
- Exactly.
- I see.

1247
00:50:37,730 --> 00:50:39,629
- We cut the grass, - Okay.

1248
00:50:39,630 --> 00:50:41,329
- truck it over, - Okay.

1249
00:50:41,330 --> 00:50:42,999
and give it to the horses.

1250
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:44,369
It's constantly getting supplies...

1251
00:50:44,370 --> 00:50:45,699
- I see.
- from the outside.

1252
00:50:45,700 --> 00:50:47,239
- Got it.
- I was in charge of...

1253
00:50:47,240 --> 00:50:48,240
weed trimming in the military.

1254
00:50:48,241 --> 00:50:50,070
I don't believe what men did in the military.

1255
00:50:50,710 --> 00:50:51,910
What are you saying?

1256
00:50:52,410 --> 00:50:54,710
I wouldn't lie about such a thing.

1257
00:50:55,340 --> 00:50:58,149
- I've got the confidence.
- You're just too tall.

1258
00:50:58,150 --> 00:51:00,050
I have a trick of my own.

1259
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:02,680
Here's the thing about me.

1260
00:51:03,180 --> 00:51:04,190
I...

1261
00:51:05,690 --> 00:51:08,289
(Heading to cut grass)

1262
00:51:08,290 --> 00:51:09,720
One horse is named Yeonjin.

1263
00:51:09,960 --> 00:51:11,229
- For real?
- Yes.

1264
00:51:11,230 --> 00:51:12,359
The horse's name is Yeonjin.

1265
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:14,200
- You were Yeonjin, right?
- Yes.

1266
00:51:14,860 --> 00:51:16,760
- You're that girl!
- Yes.

1267
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:19,129
- I had no idea.
- She was Yeonjin.

1268
00:51:19,130 --> 00:51:20,440
(Actress Shin Ye Eun, Young Park Yeon Jin in "The Glory")

1269
00:51:20,870 --> 00:51:22,339
I was right, punk.

1270
00:51:22,340 --> 00:51:24,169
You said she was just an intern.

1271
00:51:24,170 --> 00:51:25,670
(Laughing)

1272
00:51:26,070 --> 00:51:27,739
Weren't you just hit with his fist?

1273
00:51:27,740 --> 00:51:29,380
(Sung Joon got beat up.)

1274
00:51:29,580 --> 00:51:31,510
The horse's name is actually Park Yeonjin.

1275
00:51:31,910 --> 00:51:34,880
- Really?
- He's naughty and a troublemaker.

1276
00:51:35,780 --> 00:51:36,780
And so...

1277
00:51:37,590 --> 00:51:40,350
After watching that drama, he named it Yeonjin.

1278
00:51:40,490 --> 00:51:41,520
Cute.

1279
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:44,230
Does Ye Eun get a horse too?

1280
00:51:44,430 --> 00:51:45,490
Of course.

1281
00:51:46,030 --> 00:51:48,059
We can assign her to Yeonjin.

1282
00:51:48,060 --> 00:51:49,899
(Suggesting to assign Yeonjin to Ye Eun)

1283
00:51:49,900 --> 00:51:50,930
But...

1284
00:51:51,730 --> 00:51:52,870
Why are you not telling him?

1285
00:51:53,130 --> 00:51:54,770
- About what?
- That it's me.

1286
00:51:55,540 --> 00:51:56,670
Your horse is John Snow.

1287
00:51:57,040 --> 00:51:58,410
What? Wasn't it Yeonjin?

1288
00:51:58,610 --> 00:51:59,610
(Slapping)

1289
00:51:59,610 --> 00:52:00,610
We switched yesterday.

1290
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:03,180
Snow ignores me too much.

1291
00:52:03,950 --> 00:52:05,850
It may be too late.

1292
00:52:06,180 --> 00:52:07,180
I can't train him.

1293
00:52:07,181 --> 00:52:08,220
(Brightly feigning innocence)

1294
00:52:08,950 --> 00:52:11,619
The land over there. The head of the village...

1295
00:52:11,620 --> 00:52:12,649
(Morning Task Schedule: Prep feed for the pasture horses)

1296
00:52:12,650 --> 00:52:15,060
lent us about 3,306m²...

1297
00:52:15,760 --> 00:52:18,359
to grow horse feed. The grass has grown a lot.

1298
00:52:18,360 --> 00:52:19,790
The grass is different from earlier, right?

1299
00:52:20,390 --> 00:52:23,630
(It's time to cut nutrient-filled fresh grass.)

1300
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:25,030
Come this way.

1301
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:27,540
All right.

1302
00:52:27,670 --> 00:52:29,500
Here's what's important when mowing.

1303
00:52:30,100 --> 00:52:32,470
Place this near the ground,

1304
00:52:33,210 --> 00:52:36,680
and only move your waist. Only your waist, okay?

1305
00:52:36,880 --> 00:52:38,650
Your hands are to stay still.

1306
00:52:38,710 --> 00:52:40,409
- Only move your waist.
- Okay.

1307
00:52:40,410 --> 00:52:41,520
(Cutting it short with the waist is crucial.)

1308
00:52:42,480 --> 00:52:43,619
(Kwang Soo practices first.)

1309
00:52:43,620 --> 00:52:45,350
- Good.
- Just like that.

1310
00:52:45,490 --> 00:52:47,289
The trimmer doesn't have a blade, so try moving...

1311
00:52:47,290 --> 00:52:48,820
- with your waist.
- Okay.

1312
00:52:49,760 --> 00:52:50,990
Here's the important part.

1313
00:52:51,190 --> 00:52:53,259
When you're at the end, you must give it a snap.

1314
00:52:53,260 --> 00:52:54,829
It's to make the grass fall.

1315
00:52:54,830 --> 00:52:55,508
- Okay.
- Try it.

1316
00:52:55,830 --> 00:52:57,000
Move, and snap.

1317
00:52:57,300 --> 00:52:58,570
Yes, that's it.

1318
00:52:59,530 --> 00:53:01,399
Move, and snap. Come here.

1319
00:53:01,400 --> 00:53:02,400
(The former weed trimmer isn't all that bad.)

1320
00:53:02,401 --> 00:53:03,739
Okay, give it a go.

1321
00:53:03,740 --> 00:53:05,069
Pull it.

1322
00:53:05,070 --> 00:53:08,180
(Will he do well in the actual trimming?)

1323
00:53:10,510 --> 00:53:11,580
That's it.

1324
00:53:14,220 --> 00:53:15,249
You're good.

1325
00:53:15,250 --> 00:53:16,820
(Starting off steadily)

1326
00:53:17,390 --> 00:53:18,550
Lower.

1327
00:53:21,920 --> 00:53:22,920
Much lower.

1328
00:53:25,790 --> 00:53:29,400
(The CEO looks as if he had something to say.)

1329
00:53:30,330 --> 00:53:32,970
(Turning the engine off)

1330
00:53:33,970 --> 00:53:36,400
(What's going on?)

1331
00:53:37,070 --> 00:53:40,739
You'd get scolded by your father if you left rice grains...

1332
00:53:40,740 --> 00:53:43,040
in your rice bowl, wouldn't you?

1333
00:53:43,180 --> 00:53:44,410
- Yes.
- Look.

1334
00:53:45,580 --> 00:53:47,179
Watch him closely, Sung Joon.

1335
00:53:47,180 --> 00:53:50,080
(The weed trimmer got scolded.)

1336
00:53:52,290 --> 00:53:55,990
(Frustrated, the CEO starts trimming the grass himself.)

1337
00:53:56,920 --> 00:53:58,190
How would you explain this?

1338
00:53:58,290 --> 00:53:59,830
- Got it.
- I'm right, aren't I?

1339
00:54:01,330 --> 00:54:03,160
The grass over here and over there.

1340
00:54:04,200 --> 00:54:05,300
Try it again.

1341
00:54:05,870 --> 00:54:06,900
Take it off.

1342
00:54:07,270 --> 00:54:08,399
- It...
- I'll keep it in mind!

1343
00:54:08,400 --> 00:54:09,840
- Keep it in...
- Yes, sir!

1344
00:54:10,340 --> 00:54:11,370
Salute!

1345
00:54:12,210 --> 00:54:13,709
- Okay.
- I'll make sure to get it right!

1346
00:54:13,710 --> 00:54:14,779
(Finally met a true teacher)

1347
00:54:14,780 --> 00:54:16,310
I'll be sure to remember it!

1348
00:54:17,350 --> 00:54:19,679
Good. I was just joking.

1349
00:54:19,680 --> 00:54:21,719
- Sorry?
- Safety is the top priority.

1350
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:23,479
What kind of joke was that?

1351
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:24,719
Come on.

1352
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:26,550
Saying it was a joke after all that scolding?

1353
00:54:27,120 --> 00:54:29,260
Why do you have such extreme mood swings?

1354
00:54:31,460 --> 00:54:34,930
(What kind of person is the CEO?)

1355
00:54:35,030 --> 00:54:37,770
He's not trying to be mean or anything.

1356
00:54:38,030 --> 00:54:40,070
He simply says whatever comes...

1357
00:54:40,700 --> 00:54:41,999
to his mind.

1358
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,039
(His close ally says he's a nice person.)

1359
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:45,310
Was there a moment when CEO Nam Hoon...

1360
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:47,270
was being nice to you?

1361
00:54:50,010 --> 00:54:52,480
I can't remember any off the top of my head.

1362
00:54:56,080 --> 00:54:57,080
Put it on.

1363
00:54:57,081 --> 00:54:59,420
(It's Kyung Soo's turn to practice.)

1364
00:54:59,850 --> 00:55:00,889
- Just 2m.
- Okay.

1365
00:55:00,890 --> 00:55:01,920
Okay? Get it going.

1366
00:55:03,590 --> 00:55:07,160
(Turning the engine on calmly)

1367
00:55:10,770 --> 00:55:11,800
That's it.

1368
00:55:13,970 --> 00:55:15,040
Yes.

1369
00:55:18,110 --> 00:55:19,569
(The grass is piling up neatly.)

1370
00:55:19,570 --> 00:55:20,780
You're amazing at it.

1371
00:55:21,610 --> 00:55:23,579
Stop there. Don't go to the other side.

1372
00:55:23,580 --> 00:55:24,610
- Got it.
- Okay.

1373
00:55:25,380 --> 00:55:26,879
- I'll see you later.
- Bye.

1374
00:55:26,880 --> 00:55:28,349
Bye.

1375
00:55:28,350 --> 00:55:30,120
(The CEO returns to the ranch first.)

1376
00:55:31,990 --> 00:55:35,760
(Now the real training begins.)

1377
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:53,070
(Thoroughly cutting all the grass without leaving any behind)

1378
00:55:53,370 --> 00:55:55,109
- The outside first?
- Yes.

1379
00:55:55,110 --> 00:55:56,580
Do you mind coming here?

1380
00:55:56,840 --> 00:55:58,749
The roots are heavy, correct?

1381
00:55:58,750 --> 00:56:01,980
So make sure the roots face this way...

1382
00:56:02,020 --> 00:56:03,750
- when loading them first.
- Got it.

1383
00:56:11,130 --> 00:56:12,859
When loading the next batch,

1384
00:56:12,860 --> 00:56:14,359
place it so that the roots...

1385
00:56:14,360 --> 00:56:16,000
face the other side.

1386
00:56:17,330 --> 00:56:20,500
(The intern quietly loads the grass.)

1387
00:56:21,800 --> 00:56:26,540
(The trainees focus on trimming the grass.)

1388
00:56:28,380 --> 00:56:29,809
Can we...

1389
00:56:29,810 --> 00:56:32,580
really work without saying anything?

1390
00:56:33,280 --> 00:56:34,520
This is normal when we work.

1391
00:56:37,590 --> 00:56:41,289
(And so, they just kept working.)

1392
00:56:41,290 --> 00:56:42,290
(1 hour later)

1393
00:56:42,291 --> 00:56:43,360
Isn't this enough?

1394
00:56:44,290 --> 00:56:46,160
- Is this enough?
- Yes.

1395
00:56:48,260 --> 00:56:49,629
Load it all this way?

1396
00:56:49,630 --> 00:56:50,899
- No.
- This way?

1397
00:56:50,900 --> 00:56:52,000
Yes, the opposite direction.

1398
00:56:53,079 --> 00:56:54,679
Someone has to go on top...

1399
00:56:54,870 --> 00:56:56,369
- and press them down.
- Ye Eun.

1400
00:56:56,370 --> 00:56:57,370
Okay.

1401
00:56:57,371 --> 00:56:58,739
(Struggling)

1402
00:56:58,740 --> 00:56:59,769
Do I step on them?

1403
00:56:59,770 --> 00:57:01,640
Yes, just step on them.

1404
00:57:02,880 --> 00:57:05,009
- Nice.
- It has to be flattened out.

1405
00:57:05,010 --> 00:57:06,110
Correct.

1406
00:57:07,210 --> 00:57:13,050
(Now that it's flat, they load the rest of the grass.)

1407
00:57:13,750 --> 00:57:15,189
It's quite a pile now, right?

1408
00:57:15,190 --> 00:57:16,259
Yes.

1409
00:57:16,260 --> 00:57:17,420
Isn't this enough?

1410
00:57:19,190 --> 00:57:22,430
(It's time to go feed the horses.)

1411
00:57:27,370 --> 00:57:29,040
- Sung Joon.
- Yes?

1412
00:57:29,070 --> 00:57:30,100
Did anyone buy the soil?

1413
00:57:30,740 --> 00:57:31,770
Yes.

1414
00:57:31,870 --> 00:57:32,940
Do they buy it often?

1415
00:57:33,610 --> 00:57:35,279
Customers often buy it in small batches.

1416
00:57:35,280 --> 00:57:37,080
(Asking about sales on the thrifting app)

1417
00:57:37,140 --> 00:57:38,579
Give us your feedback on what we wrote.

1418
00:57:38,580 --> 00:57:41,380
We weren't sure what people here would be like.

1419
00:57:42,020 --> 00:57:43,279
- Give it a listen.
- Okay.

1420
00:57:43,280 --> 00:57:44,719
(Asking for feedback)

1421
00:57:44,720 --> 00:57:47,560
"Premium potting soil for sale."

1422
00:57:47,720 --> 00:57:50,059
"Use it in your garden or when repotting..."

1423
00:57:50,060 --> 00:57:52,890
"to give your plants a healthy new home."

1424
00:57:53,230 --> 00:57:55,099
"With our premium potting soil,"

1425
00:57:55,100 --> 00:57:56,830
"transplant shock is a thing of the past."

1426
00:57:57,060 --> 00:57:58,829
"Hi. I'm actually Jack..."

1427
00:57:58,830 --> 00:58:00,430
"from 'Jack and the Beanstalk.'"

1428
00:58:01,070 --> 00:58:02,999
"You've heard about it, right?"

1429
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:04,000
(Here's the problematic part.)

1430
00:58:04,340 --> 00:58:05,970
"You've heard about me, right?"

1431
00:58:06,210 --> 00:58:08,209
"What helped grow the beanstalk so tall..."

1432
00:58:08,210 --> 00:58:10,980
"wasn't the magical seed. It was this very soil."

1433
00:58:11,850 --> 00:58:15,080
(He can't stop laughing.)

1434
00:58:15,580 --> 00:58:17,350
What?

1435
00:58:17,550 --> 00:58:19,150
(Questioning what she had just read)

1436
00:58:19,520 --> 00:58:22,689
"Hi. I'm actually Jack from 'Jack and the Beanstalk.'"

1437
00:58:22,690 --> 00:58:23,690
That sounds so lame.

1438
00:58:24,190 --> 00:58:25,230
What does that mean?

1439
00:58:26,030 --> 00:58:27,800
It sounds like someone old wrote it, right?

1440
00:58:28,330 --> 00:58:30,330
Should I say it's out of style?

1441
00:58:30,600 --> 00:58:31,700
Kwang Soo.

1442
00:58:32,030 --> 00:58:33,070
Why...

1443
00:58:33,670 --> 00:58:35,899
- You're a goner now.
- Nonsense.

1444
00:58:35,900 --> 00:58:37,069
Edit it. Just take it out.

1445
00:58:37,070 --> 00:58:38,240
"Jack and the Beanstalk."

1446
00:58:38,910 --> 00:58:40,609
- Hurry up and take that part out.
- The flow...

1447
00:58:40,610 --> 00:58:41,980
of the paragraphs...

1448
00:58:42,140 --> 00:58:43,140
What did you think?

1449
00:58:43,510 --> 00:58:45,780
- Compared to the others.
- It's too long.

1450
00:58:45,880 --> 00:58:47,409
Is it? Should it be short?

1451
00:58:47,410 --> 00:58:48,420
(Sung Joon is against it.)

1452
00:58:48,550 --> 00:58:49,550
Do I take this out?

1453
00:58:49,551 --> 00:58:51,149
"Time reveals the difference you can't see."

1454
00:58:51,150 --> 00:58:52,220
Do I?

1455
00:58:52,990 --> 00:58:54,289
What do you mean by that?

1456
00:58:54,290 --> 00:58:56,320
(It needs a complete revision.)

1457
00:58:57,520 --> 00:58:58,530
Did you get an order?

1458
00:58:58,690 --> 00:58:59,730
- No.
- The soil condition...

1459
00:59:00,160 --> 00:59:02,059
Our text is too long, so we're editing it.

1460
00:59:02,060 --> 00:59:03,760
Something like, "The new product..."

1461
00:59:04,160 --> 00:59:05,830
"Amazing soil on sale."

1462
00:59:06,370 --> 00:59:09,239
"Selling nutritious soil for gardening and landscaping."

1463
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:10,939
- I keep getting messages.
- Show me.

1464
00:59:10,940 --> 00:59:12,009
You're right.

1465
00:59:12,010 --> 00:59:13,370
"I'm texting you about the soil."

1466
00:59:13,740 --> 00:59:14,909
So it actually works.

1467
00:59:14,910 --> 00:59:16,810
(We also need to get an order.)

1468
00:59:18,180 --> 00:59:24,420
(Meanwhile, at the ranch)

1469
00:59:27,190 --> 00:59:33,790
(The hungry horses are gathering around.)

1470
00:59:36,860 --> 00:59:39,800
(When is our food coming?)

1471
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:46,310
(War might break out if they don't hurry with the food.)

1472
00:59:46,510 --> 00:59:47,779
It's time now.

1473
00:59:47,780 --> 00:59:50,380
(The delivery has begun.)

1474
00:59:50,910 --> 00:59:54,780
(Entering the ranch slowly)

1475
00:59:55,320 --> 00:59:57,150
Gosh. Look, Ye Eun.

1476
00:59:59,090 --> 01:00:01,559
- Aren't they huge?
- Did we come here today?

1477
01:00:01,560 --> 01:00:03,219
(Such a sight is a first.)

1478
01:00:03,220 --> 01:00:04,690
Let's go!

1479
01:00:05,060 --> 01:00:08,160
(Calling the horses)

1480
01:00:09,430 --> 01:00:11,530
Let's eat!

1481
01:00:12,530 --> 01:00:15,670
(The horses are nowhere to be seen.)

1482
01:00:17,300 --> 01:00:20,510
(Speeding up without any horses following them)

1483
01:00:21,610 --> 01:00:25,110
(Unsure of what's going on at first)

1484
01:00:26,410 --> 01:00:27,450
Here they come.

1485
01:00:28,720 --> 01:00:30,050
- Are they? Yes, from over there.
- Gosh.

1486
01:00:30,580 --> 01:00:31,690
I'm taking photos.

1487
01:00:32,450 --> 01:00:35,620
(Shocked at something)

1488
01:00:36,590 --> 01:00:38,230
They're running alongside the car.

1489
01:00:39,790 --> 01:00:43,899
(The horses run along with the car.)

1490
01:00:43,900 --> 01:00:47,030
- Let's eat!
- Come and eat!

1491
01:00:51,010 --> 01:00:53,270
- Mamama!
- Mamama!

1492
01:00:53,910 --> 01:00:56,980
(Upon hearing that the food is here,)

1493
01:00:58,480 --> 01:01:00,749
(the horses come to greet them from all four sides of the ranch.)

1494
01:01:00,750 --> 01:01:02,219
Let's eat!

1495
01:01:02,220 --> 01:01:05,090
(They can't take their eyes off the sight.)

1496
01:01:06,220 --> 01:01:08,290
They're coming. All of them are following us.

1497
01:01:12,690 --> 01:01:16,600
(I have to film this.)

1498
01:01:17,260 --> 01:01:18,270
There are more over here.

1499
01:01:18,670 --> 01:01:21,700
(Meeting their horse friends on the other side)

1500
01:01:22,300 --> 01:01:23,370
They're coming up.

1501
01:01:25,570 --> 01:01:27,070
How many horses are there?

1502
01:01:27,170 --> 01:01:28,180
They're coming.

1503
01:01:30,910 --> 01:01:33,009
Look at that pony over there.

1504
01:01:33,010 --> 01:01:35,580
(A little walk before their meal)

1505
01:01:35,620 --> 01:01:36,980
They're running.

1506
01:01:37,520 --> 01:01:38,790
(Mamama!)

1507
01:01:38,920 --> 01:01:40,190
Run!

1508
01:01:42,790 --> 01:01:44,019
Let's go.

1509
01:01:44,020 --> 01:01:46,560
(When you tell them to run, they really run.)

1510
01:01:46,760 --> 01:01:48,360
They look amazing.

1511
01:01:49,300 --> 01:01:52,600
(Thanks to the horses galloping right before their eyes)

1512
01:01:52,800 --> 01:01:54,229
(Screaming)

1513
01:01:54,230 --> 01:01:56,770
(The trainees are super excited.)

1514
01:01:56,940 --> 01:01:59,410
(He's also excited.)

1515
01:02:00,070 --> 01:02:02,179
(When they hear "mamama")

1516
01:02:02,180 --> 01:02:03,339
(A magical signal that makes them run faster)

1517
01:02:03,340 --> 01:02:04,579
They're running.

1518
01:02:04,580 --> 01:02:07,150
(A magical signal that makes them run faster)

1519
01:02:08,720 --> 01:02:12,950
(Humans and horses riding at full speed)

1520
01:02:15,360 --> 01:02:17,860
Mamama!

1521
01:02:20,530 --> 01:02:26,229
(They reach the top of the mountain after a refreshing run.)

1522
01:02:26,230 --> 01:02:27,630
Let's eat.

1523
01:02:28,470 --> 01:02:29,640
Let's eat.

1524
01:02:30,440 --> 01:02:33,439
I'll give you food.

1525
01:02:33,440 --> 01:02:35,440
- Let's go.
- Let's eat.

1526
01:02:36,440 --> 01:02:37,780
Let's eat.

1527
01:02:38,150 --> 01:02:41,179
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

1528
01:02:41,180 --> 01:02:42,379
(Running together makes breakfast taste even better.)

1529
01:02:42,380 --> 01:02:43,820
Let's eat.

1530
01:02:44,650 --> 01:02:47,320
(While handing out grass,)

1531
01:02:47,920 --> 01:02:50,090
(Kwang Soo gathers a huge bundle of grass.)

1532
01:02:51,260 --> 01:02:52,629
Let's eat!

1533
01:02:52,630 --> 01:02:53,630
(He throws it without warning.)

1534
01:02:54,900 --> 01:02:55,900
Gosh.

1535
01:02:55,901 --> 01:02:57,160
(Ye Eun gets covered by it while passing by.)

1536
01:02:57,730 --> 01:02:59,169
Ye Eun, don't get me wrong.

1537
01:02:59,170 --> 01:03:01,500
I threw it first, and you walked into it.

1538
01:03:03,040 --> 01:03:04,040
I'm sorry...

1539
01:03:04,270 --> 01:03:05,270
It's okay.

1540
01:03:05,840 --> 01:03:06,840
(The intern just laughs it off.)

1541
01:03:06,841 --> 01:03:08,040
Come here and eat.

1542
01:03:09,340 --> 01:03:10,739
Let's eat.

1543
01:03:10,740 --> 01:03:12,810
(Is he gathering another bundle of grass?)

1544
01:03:12,980 --> 01:03:14,519
Let's eat.

1545
01:03:14,520 --> 01:03:15,520
(This time, he throws it towards someone.)

1546
01:03:15,880 --> 01:03:17,320
Let's eat.

1547
01:03:19,550 --> 01:03:21,790
(There's definitely some intention behind it.)

1548
01:03:22,220 --> 01:03:24,390
(Laughing)

1549
01:03:25,060 --> 01:03:29,530
(There he goes again.)

1550
01:03:31,170 --> 01:03:32,499
Let's eat.

1551
01:03:32,500 --> 01:03:34,229
(Now it's time to properly serve breakfast again.)

1552
01:03:34,230 --> 01:03:35,940
Mamama.

1553
01:03:37,100 --> 01:03:38,440
Let's eat.

1554
01:03:38,540 --> 01:03:40,670
(Enjoying breakfast on top of the mountain)

1555
01:03:42,740 --> 01:03:44,810
Come here. Mamama.

1556
01:03:45,710 --> 01:03:46,949
Bring over a big bundle of grass.

1557
01:03:46,950 --> 01:03:49,449
The lower ranking ones can't eat because they get pushed aside.

1558
01:03:49,450 --> 01:03:50,450
Okay.

1559
01:03:50,680 --> 01:03:51,720
Have some grass.

1560
01:03:56,590 --> 01:03:58,990
(Everyone enjoys breakfast together.)

1561
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:02,760
They're so cute.

1562
01:04:03,830 --> 01:04:05,630
Shouldn't we brush his back?

1563
01:04:06,500 --> 01:04:07,729
I think someone put that on him on purpose.

1564
01:04:07,730 --> 01:04:08,770
Really?

1565
01:04:09,540 --> 01:04:11,910
(They grow even closer to the horses.)

1566
01:04:12,940 --> 01:04:13,940
Isn't this so romantic?

1567
01:04:13,941 --> 01:04:15,209
It's great to see them eat so well.

1568
01:04:15,210 --> 01:04:16,240
I know.

1569
01:04:16,380 --> 01:04:19,880
(We're grateful that the horses enjoy it.)

1570
01:04:20,180 --> 01:04:21,319
Look at him rubbing himself.

1571
01:04:21,320 --> 01:04:22,849
Look at him rubbing himself on the grass.

1572
01:04:22,850 --> 01:04:24,279
- He's claiming that it's his.
- That's so cute.

1573
01:04:24,280 --> 01:04:26,149
- He must be excited.
- When there's a lot to eat,

1574
01:04:26,150 --> 01:04:27,889
they rub themselves on it to claim it theirs.

1575
01:04:27,890 --> 01:04:29,020
He's lying down.

1576
01:04:29,220 --> 01:04:31,189
Why is he lying down all of a sudden? He must be in a good mood.

1577
01:04:31,190 --> 01:04:32,330
(How do you feel now?)

1578
01:04:32,590 --> 01:04:34,030
It's very refreshing,

1579
01:04:34,700 --> 01:04:36,360
and the horses are adorable.

1580
01:04:36,930 --> 01:04:39,000
Seeing him roll around earlier...

1581
01:04:40,100 --> 01:04:41,270
made me feel proud.

1582
01:04:42,440 --> 01:04:43,700
We cut fresh grass ourselves...

1583
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:46,040
and brought it here to feed them.

1584
01:04:46,310 --> 01:04:47,610
It was rewarding.

1585
01:04:48,110 --> 01:04:50,340
(A meal that felt more special as they harvested it themselves)

1586
01:04:51,310 --> 01:04:53,879
Cutting the grass would have been different...

1587
01:04:53,880 --> 01:04:55,820
if we had done this first.

1588
01:04:57,450 --> 01:04:59,190
We should've brought more.

1589
01:05:01,220 --> 01:05:04,160
We should've brought some more with our own car.

1590
01:05:04,460 --> 01:05:08,500
(The trainees have grown much closer to the horses.)

1591
01:05:10,360 --> 01:05:12,430
- This place is beautiful.
- It really is.

1592
01:05:16,240 --> 01:05:19,240
