- And intestine soup.

1645
01:07:08,450 --> 01:07:09,680
Intestine soup?

1646
01:07:10,420 --> 01:07:12,290
Are you getting hangover soup or intestine soup?

1647
01:07:13,390 --> 01:07:14,390
Hangover soup.

1648
01:07:14,520 --> 01:07:15,889
- What are you getting?
- What should I get?

1649
01:07:15,890 --> 01:07:16,960
It's driving me crazy.

1650
01:07:17,520 --> 01:07:20,490
(Choosing is even harder because there are only 2 options.)

1651
01:07:21,760 --> 01:07:24,769
(Attempting to spy on the next table)

1652
01:07:24,770 --> 01:07:26,330
One is white, and the other is red.

1653
01:07:26,600 --> 01:07:29,640
(It's harder to decide because they're very different.)

1654
01:07:30,370 --> 01:07:31,410
Intestine?

1655
01:07:32,140 --> 01:07:33,210
Are you getting intestine soup?

1656
01:07:34,370 --> 01:07:35,410
Intestine.

1657
01:07:36,640 --> 01:07:41,210
(The menu choices are split perfectly 1-to-1.)

1658
01:07:41,420 --> 01:07:42,450
I'm getting intestine soup.

1659
01:07:45,190 --> 01:07:46,190
No, hangover soup.

1660
01:07:47,090 --> 01:07:48,090
Intestine soup.

1661
01:07:48,091 --> 01:07:50,060
(Kwang Soo can't make up his mind.)

1662
01:07:50,590 --> 01:07:52,060
Intestine soup.

1663
01:07:52,430 --> 01:07:54,060
We'll get two orders of intestine soup.

1664
01:07:57,660 --> 01:07:59,270
- Are you bad at playing games?
- Yes.

1665
01:08:00,630 --> 01:08:02,170
Ye Eun is unlucky.

1666
01:08:03,470 --> 01:08:04,500
How about this?

1667
01:08:04,940 --> 01:08:06,340
We'll run the stopwatch.

1668
01:08:06,610 --> 01:08:07,870
The loser has to take a bite of this.

1669
01:08:08,240 --> 01:08:09,580
About one-third of it.

1670
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:10,910
This part isn't spicy, is it?

1671
01:08:11,240 --> 01:08:12,510
Right. Eating one-third of it.

1672
01:08:12,980 --> 01:08:15,279
Shall we play? Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

1673
01:08:15,280 --> 01:08:16,480
(Cheongyang chili stopwatch starts.)

1674
01:08:16,880 --> 01:08:18,719
(Kyung Soo, Ye Eun, Kwang Soo)

1675
01:08:18,720 --> 01:08:19,720
Six.

1676
01:08:20,850 --> 01:08:22,290
Three. Eighteen.

1677
01:08:24,190 --> 01:08:25,190
Stop.

1678
01:08:25,690 --> 01:08:26,690
Five.

1679
01:08:26,691 --> 01:08:27,929
(Meanwhile, he adds some garlic.)

1680
01:08:27,930 --> 01:08:29,200
You should get over four.

1681
01:08:29,760 --> 01:08:31,699
(Ye Eun, 5 times 6 equals 30.)

1682
01:08:31,700 --> 01:08:32,730
- What?
- Thirty?

1683
01:08:33,030 --> 01:08:34,030
Goodness.

1684
01:08:34,031 --> 01:08:36,600
(The intern may be unlucky, but she's ahead of them.)

1685
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:39,170
- Isn't yours 18?
- Yes, 6 times 3 is 18.

1686
01:08:40,940 --> 01:08:43,910
(Kwang Soo, 0)

1687
01:08:44,210 --> 01:08:45,210
Okay.

1688
01:08:46,950 --> 01:08:48,009
He lost.

1689
01:08:48,010 --> 01:08:51,380
(Kwang Soo loses in an instant.)

1690
01:08:53,090 --> 01:08:55,090
This must be really spicy.

1691
01:08:56,390 --> 01:08:58,389
(It's even spicier because of the garlic added secretly.)

1692
01:08:58,390 --> 01:08:59,660
It must be piquant at the end.

1693
01:09:00,430 --> 01:09:01,460
I'm so happy.

1694
01:09:01,730 --> 01:09:03,560
Let's eat. Eat up, Ye Eun.

1695
01:09:04,800 --> 01:09:06,869
- His eyes are tearing up.
- Bon appetit.

1696
01:09:06,870 --> 01:09:08,299
- Thank you for the food.
- Enjoy your meal.

1697
01:09:08,300 --> 01:09:09,900
- Enjoy.
- It's really good.

1698
01:09:10,670 --> 01:09:12,209
There's aged kimchi in it.

1699
01:09:12,210 --> 01:09:13,210
(Leaving tears behind, they start eating the hangover soup.)

1700
01:09:13,810 --> 01:09:14,840
It looks so good.

1701
01:09:19,280 --> 01:09:20,749
(Exclaiming)

1702
01:09:20,750 --> 01:09:21,820
It's good.

1703
01:09:25,050 --> 01:09:26,050
Yum.

1704
01:09:30,120 --> 01:09:31,760
(Impressed)

1705
01:09:34,330 --> 01:09:35,960
Gosh, it tastes good.

1706
01:09:36,060 --> 01:09:37,860
- It's got a nice spicy kick.
- Yes.

1707
01:09:38,570 --> 01:09:40,230
This is what we needed right now.

1708
01:09:40,700 --> 01:09:42,569
(The perfect warm and spicy soup for a rainy day)

1709
01:09:42,570 --> 01:09:43,769
It's really refreshing.

1710
01:09:43,770 --> 01:09:45,940
(The perfect warm and spicy soup for a rainy day)

1711
01:09:46,370 --> 01:09:49,340
Try it with some chives in it.

1712
01:09:50,240 --> 01:09:54,450
(As told by the Food Director, she adds chives.)

1713
01:09:55,750 --> 01:09:58,250
(When you take a bite with some chives)

1714
01:09:58,990 --> 01:10:00,850
(The taste makes you applaud.)

1715
01:10:01,590 --> 01:10:02,590
It's good.

1716
01:10:04,290 --> 01:10:07,760
(CEO Lee is devouring glass noodles.)

1717
01:10:08,230 --> 01:10:09,360
It's very good.

1718
01:10:10,360 --> 01:10:12,169
(Every sip of the broth is touching.)

1719
01:10:12,170 --> 01:10:13,300
This hangover soup is insane.

1720
01:10:14,600 --> 01:10:17,340
(Enjoying it with clotted blood)

1721
01:10:17,370 --> 01:10:19,540
The clotted blood tastes good. It doesn't smell bad.

1722
01:10:20,240 --> 01:10:21,810
(He totally agrees.)

1723
01:10:22,440 --> 01:10:28,950
(It perfectly suits the intern's taste.)

1724
01:10:30,180 --> 01:10:33,450
(This deserves a photo.)

1725
01:10:34,250 --> 01:10:38,530
(She takes a photo of the plate instead of the earthen pot.)

1726
01:10:39,730 --> 01:10:40,730
(Kwang Soo notices what she's doing.)

1727
01:10:40,731 --> 01:10:43,030
Ye Eun, isn't your photo...

1728
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:45,429
What's wrong?

1729
01:10:45,430 --> 01:10:47,399
Shouldn't you make the food look appetizing?

1730
01:10:47,400 --> 01:10:48,970
I'm bad at taking photos of food.

1731
01:10:49,870 --> 01:10:51,240
But this is...

1732
01:10:51,810 --> 01:10:53,040
quite terrible.

1733
01:10:53,910 --> 01:10:55,640
(How did her photo turn out?)

1734
01:10:57,780 --> 01:10:59,580
- What's that?
- I just need to know what it is.

1735
01:11:02,050 --> 01:11:03,080
Is it bad?

1736
01:11:03,780 --> 01:11:05,119
I think it came out well.

1737
01:11:05,120 --> 01:11:06,250
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1738
01:11:07,850 --> 01:11:09,320
The rain doesn't stop.

1739
01:11:09,590 --> 01:11:10,760
It's raining so much.

1740
01:11:11,420 --> 01:11:13,829
(After lunch, the trainees are back at the ranch.)

1741
01:11:13,830 --> 01:11:14,830
That's Yeonjin.

1742
01:11:15,300 --> 01:11:16,859
- On the left?
- Yes.

1743
01:11:16,860 --> 01:11:18,200
(Yeonjin and Jacy who's pregnant)

1744
01:11:18,500 --> 01:11:20,270
She went over the fence.

1745
01:11:21,200 --> 01:11:22,200
- Again?
- That's cute.

1746
01:11:22,201 --> 01:11:24,900
(Yeonjin got caught at someone else's house.)

1747
01:11:25,640 --> 01:11:26,909
Kwang Soo, please help.

1748
01:11:26,910 --> 01:11:28,880
Jacy's veterinarian is here.

1749
01:11:29,410 --> 01:11:31,510
- Take Jacy to the veterinarian.
- Okay.

1750
01:11:32,310 --> 01:11:34,080
Whoa, hold on.

1751
01:11:34,380 --> 01:11:37,580
(He takes Jacy to the veterinarian for the upcoming labor.)

1752
01:11:38,950 --> 01:11:40,890
- Kwang Soo, she'll go in here.
- Okay.

1753
01:11:41,150 --> 01:11:42,320
In here.

1754
01:11:42,720 --> 01:11:43,720
Okay.

1755
01:11:43,920 --> 01:11:45,429
(Meanwhile, Yeonjin)

1756
01:11:45,430 --> 01:11:47,760
Yeonjin, I'm also Yeon Jin.

1757
01:11:47,960 --> 01:11:50,800
(She met another Yeonjin for the first time.)

1758
01:11:50,900 --> 01:11:53,269
Ye Eun, could you take Yeonjin to pasture?

1759
01:11:53,270 --> 01:11:55,340
Jacy will get stressed out because Yeonjin is male.

1760
01:11:56,100 --> 01:11:57,139
Come here and eat grass.

1761
01:11:57,140 --> 01:11:59,239
Take him out there to pasture for a while.

1762
01:11:59,240 --> 01:12:00,240
Okay.

1763
01:12:01,040 --> 01:12:03,609
Come on. Let's go.

1764
01:12:03,610 --> 01:12:06,180
- All right. Good girl.
- Let's go.

1765
01:12:06,710 --> 01:12:07,710
Okay.

1766
01:12:07,711 --> 01:12:09,520
(Kwang Soo brings her to the riding area safely.)

1767
01:12:10,120 --> 01:12:11,179
Hello, sir.

1768
01:12:11,180 --> 01:12:12,990
- Hello.
- Hello.

1769
01:12:13,590 --> 01:12:14,920
You came a long way.

1770
01:12:15,120 --> 01:12:17,060
Kwang Soo, can you put one more in the back?

1771
01:12:17,560 --> 01:12:18,729
(Meanwhile, Kyung Soo)

1772
01:12:18,730 --> 01:12:20,889
Stay next to Kyung Soo and brush her.

1773
01:12:20,890 --> 01:12:21,900
Okay.

1774
01:12:22,600 --> 01:12:25,430
(Relaxing Jacy by brushing before the checkup)

1775
01:12:25,970 --> 01:12:28,740
(Meanwhile, the veterinarian finishes getting ready.)

1776
01:12:30,440 --> 01:12:33,109
(First, checking the pulse)

1777
01:12:33,110 --> 01:12:35,479
I'll insert the thermometer now. Please step back.

1778
01:12:35,480 --> 01:12:38,910
Hang in there for a minute. That's good.

1779
01:12:39,610 --> 01:12:40,709
All right.

1780
01:12:40,710 --> 01:12:42,180
I checked her temperature.

1781
01:12:43,020 --> 01:12:44,450
Her temperature is normal.

1782
01:12:45,390 --> 01:12:46,720
Her pulse is good.

1783
01:12:47,620 --> 01:12:49,790
In horses, the uterus is located directly below the rectum.

1784
01:12:50,460 --> 01:12:52,090
I'll insert my hand into the rectum...

1785
01:12:52,690 --> 01:12:55,700
to check the condition of the fetus.

1786
01:12:57,436 --> 01:12:58,876
Ye Eun, get the shovel ready on this side.

1787
01:12:59,300 --> 01:13:01,499
The veterinarian will remove the poop first.

1788
01:13:01,500 --> 01:13:02,670
Please collect it from the side.

1789
01:13:04,240 --> 01:13:07,209
(It's time to check the fetus.)

1790
01:13:07,210 --> 01:13:08,210
A little to the back.

1791
01:13:08,211 --> 01:13:11,240
(The veterinarian inserted his hand into the rectum.)

1792
01:13:12,810 --> 01:13:15,320
(An incredible sight that she's never seen before)

1793
01:13:15,580 --> 01:13:17,280
Gosh. Could you get closer?

1794
01:13:17,950 --> 01:13:19,190
(Dropping)

1795
01:13:19,590 --> 01:13:20,920
Why is he taking out the poop?

1796
01:13:22,420 --> 01:13:25,930
I need to remove the manure so I can feel the foal with my hand.

1797
01:13:26,560 --> 01:13:28,930
The rectum is right here.

1798
01:13:29,630 --> 01:13:31,629
The uterus is located right underneath it.

1799
01:13:31,630 --> 01:13:32,800
I see.

1800
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:35,540
When I put my hand into the rectum,

1801
01:13:35,870 --> 01:13:37,370
I can feel the foal inside the uterus.

1802
01:13:37,940 --> 01:13:40,739
The foal is inside the uterus.

1803
01:13:40,740 --> 01:13:42,310
When I put my hand in...

1804
01:13:43,540 --> 01:13:45,849
(He checks the location of the foal.)

1805
01:13:45,850 --> 01:13:47,649
The head is on this side.

1806
01:13:47,650 --> 01:13:49,680
The hind end is in the back.

1807
01:13:50,180 --> 01:13:51,679
When I press on the head,

1808
01:13:51,680 --> 01:13:53,820
the foal responds.

1809
01:13:54,350 --> 01:13:57,019
How can he touch the foal like that?

1810
01:13:57,020 --> 01:13:59,460
(A fascinating way to check the foal by hand)

1811
01:13:59,890 --> 01:14:01,589
Sir, how is the mother doing?

1812
01:14:01,590 --> 01:14:03,860
(Question 1 after the checkup, Jacy's health)

1813
01:14:04,100 --> 01:14:05,870
Her intestines are good.

1814
01:14:06,430 --> 01:14:07,630
Her heart sounds healthy.

1815
01:14:07,730 --> 01:14:09,970
Overall, she's in good condition.

1816
01:14:10,340 --> 01:14:12,410
(Based on the result, Jacy is healthy.)

1817
01:14:12,710 --> 01:14:14,009
(Patting gently)

1818
01:14:14,010 --> 01:14:16,080
Well done.

1819
01:14:16,810 --> 01:14:18,510
It's over, Jacy.

1820
01:14:19,080 --> 01:14:20,080
It's all over.

1821
01:14:20,310 --> 01:14:22,619
About a day away from giving birth,

1822
01:14:22,620 --> 01:14:26,849
the muscles and ligaments around the tail start to relax.

1823
01:14:26,850 --> 01:14:28,090
They become soft.

1824
01:14:28,660 --> 01:14:29,920
They're already very soft.

1825
01:14:29,945 --> 01:14:31,708
They will become even softer.

1826
01:14:33,160 --> 01:14:35,089
She still has some time before giving birth.

1827
01:14:35,090 --> 01:14:37,200
So it won't be tonight, will it?

1828
01:14:37,940 --> 01:14:39,349
I don't think it'll be tonight.

1829
01:14:39,870 --> 01:14:42,039
(It doesn't look like labor is imminent.)

1830
01:14:42,040 --> 01:14:43,240
- How about tomorrow?
- Are you disappointed?

1831
01:14:43,840 --> 01:14:44,840
We'll see tomorrow.

1832
01:14:44,970 --> 01:14:47,639
Even if it's not tonight, could it be tomorrow?

1833
01:14:47,640 --> 01:14:49,109
Of course. We have to observe every day.

1834
01:14:49,110 --> 01:14:50,179
I see.

1835
01:14:50,180 --> 01:14:51,950
(She'll need continued monitoring.)

1836
01:14:52,210 --> 01:14:53,850
Since you're here,

1837
01:14:53,980 --> 01:14:55,919
- would you happen to need soil?
- What?

1838
01:14:55,920 --> 01:14:57,449
- Soil.
- What soil?

1839
01:14:57,450 --> 01:14:58,920
Do you grow any potted plants?

1840
01:14:59,320 --> 01:15:00,320
Landscaping soil.

1841
01:15:00,321 --> 01:15:01,919
I run a farm, so I have plenty of soil...

1842
01:15:01,920 --> 01:15:03,659
- at home.
- I see.

1843
01:15:03,660 --> 01:15:05,389
I also have a horse ranch.

1844
01:15:05,390 --> 01:15:06,790
- Is that right?
- Yes.

1845
01:15:07,730 --> 01:15:09,600
Are you active on thrifting app called Karrot?

1846
01:15:09,900 --> 01:15:11,759
No, I don't grow any carrots.

1847
01:15:11,760 --> 01:15:13,999
No, I don't mean growing carrots.

1848
01:15:14,000 --> 01:15:16,239
- No, it's a marketplace.
- A marketplace for used goods.

1849
01:15:16,240 --> 01:15:18,169
We sell soil in that marketplace.

1850
01:15:18,170 --> 01:15:20,239
- I'll spread the word.
- Okay.

1851
01:15:20,240 --> 01:15:22,479
- My ID is Yeonjin's Dad.
- "Yeonjin's Dad?"

1852
01:15:22,480 --> 01:15:24,609
- Please feel free to contact me.
- All right.

1853
01:15:24,610 --> 01:15:26,109
Thank you. Take care.

1854
01:15:26,110 --> 01:15:27,310
(After promoting their compost, the checkup ends.)

1855
01:15:28,150 --> 01:15:29,480
Ye Eun, will you lead her?

1856
01:15:30,020 --> 01:15:32,120
We'll take her back out to the pasture.

1857
01:15:33,150 --> 01:15:35,289
Ye Eun, this is Jacy's zone.

1858
01:15:35,290 --> 01:15:36,660
- Is this her home?
- Yes.

1859
01:15:36,990 --> 01:15:38,259
Does she live here alone?

1860
01:15:38,260 --> 01:15:39,260
Alone.

1861
01:15:39,261 --> 01:15:40,759
- It's because...
- To prepare herself?

1862
01:15:40,760 --> 01:15:41,760
Okay.

1863
01:15:42,600 --> 01:15:44,330
Have a healthy foal.

1864
01:15:44,700 --> 01:15:45,700
Go in.

1865
01:15:46,000 --> 01:15:47,000
My gosh.

1866
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:49,470
She looks amazing.

1867
01:15:50,400 --> 01:15:51,539
She looks free.

1868
01:15:51,540 --> 01:15:54,210
(That's how Jacy's checkup ended.)

1869
01:15:55,340 --> 01:15:57,810
(A few days later)

1870
01:15:57,910 --> 01:15:59,650
The baby is coming out right now.

1871
01:16:00,180 --> 01:16:01,310
Let's go, Jacy.

1872
01:16:01,680 --> 01:16:02,880
You can do it.

1873
01:16:07,590 --> 01:16:09,390
My goodness.

1874
01:16:13,890 --> 01:16:15,159
Don't we need to take it out?

1875
01:16:15,160 --> 01:16:17,000
(After lying for a short rest)

1876
01:16:17,200 --> 01:16:18,670
Good job, Jacy.

1877
01:16:18,830 --> 01:16:19,999
You can do it, Jacy.

1878
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:21,000
(Jacy gathers her strength again.)

1879
01:16:21,200 --> 01:16:23,170
That's it. The baby is coming out.

1880
01:16:24,170 --> 01:16:25,269
Gosh, Jacy.

1881
01:16:25,270 --> 01:16:26,669
It's out.

1882
01:16:26,670 --> 01:16:28,510
- The foal is out.
- It's out. Well done.

1883
01:16:31,780 --> 01:16:33,180
Well done.

1884
01:16:34,350 --> 01:16:38,279
(Jacy welcomed a new life safely into this world.)

1885
01:16:38,280 --> 01:16:40,549
(Back to the present)

1886
01:16:40,550 --> 01:16:41,550
Yeonjin.

1887
01:16:42,490 --> 01:16:43,767
Let's get some grass together.

1888
01:16:43,990 --> 01:16:46,330
(Led by Older Yeon Jin, they head toward the field.)

1889
01:16:47,260 --> 01:16:49,629
- His name is Yeonjin.
- Right.

1890
01:16:49,630 --> 01:16:51,629
They named him Yeonjin because he always gets in trouble.

1891
01:16:51,630 --> 01:16:52,800
(Laughing)

1892
01:16:52,930 --> 01:16:54,369
(Stopping)

1893
01:16:54,370 --> 01:16:55,540
Keep your eyes forward.

1894
01:16:55,840 --> 01:16:58,440
(Older Yeon Jin keeps her younger sibling in line.)

1895
01:16:59,050 --> 01:17:00,076
Where are you going?

1896
01:17:01,340 --> 01:17:04,310
(A typical teenager pretends not to hear.)

1897
01:17:04,335 --> 01:17:05,375
No, come this way.

1898
01:17:05,763 --> 01:17:06,833
Mamama.

1899
01:17:07,380 --> 01:17:08,919
Mamama.

1900
01:17:08,920 --> 01:17:10,950
(The two Yeonjins are busy bickering.)

1901
01:17:11,620 --> 01:17:13,020
Yeonjin, have some grass.

1902
01:17:13,750 --> 01:17:15,090
It's time to graze.

1903
01:17:15,964 --> 01:17:16,826
Are you thirsty?

1904
01:17:17,220 --> 01:17:18,990
I'll let you graze.

1905
01:17:19,330 --> 01:17:20,859
(He refuses to graze and goes back.)

1906
01:17:20,860 --> 01:17:22,560
(Being dragged)

1907
01:17:22,860 --> 01:17:24,530
You can't run all of a sudden.

1908
01:17:24,800 --> 01:17:25,800
No.

1909
01:17:26,600 --> 01:17:27,600
No!

1910
01:17:29,640 --> 01:17:30,640
Please stop him.

1911
01:17:34,870 --> 01:17:37,240
(The teenage sibling's rebellion finally explodes.)

1912
01:17:37,440 --> 01:17:38,510
No.

1913
01:17:38,810 --> 01:17:39,810
Gosh.

1914
01:17:39,980 --> 01:17:42,050
(Watching the fight taking place behind a horse)

1915
01:17:42,150 --> 01:17:43,480
Gosh, he's really fast.

1916
01:17:44,620 --> 01:17:45,750
Park Yeonjin!

1917
01:17:46,690 --> 01:17:50,519
(Yeonjin is being Yeonjin.)

1918
01:17:50,520 --> 01:17:51,890
He's really something.

1919
01:17:54,430 --> 01:17:55,760
That little rascal.

1920
01:17:58,200 --> 01:18:01,000
(Before they know it, the final day of training arrives.)

1921
01:18:01,600 --> 01:18:04,400
(They've grown closer to the horses.)

1922
01:18:04,870 --> 01:18:07,640
(They're all smiles with the ranch staff.)

1923
01:18:07,870 --> 01:18:09,009
(In a cheerful atmosphere)

1924
01:18:09,010 --> 01:18:10,010
(Achick!)

1925
01:18:10,011 --> 01:18:11,180
(With the ranch family)

1926
01:18:11,640 --> 01:18:13,750
(A game with the dinner bill on the line starts.)

1927
01:18:14,150 --> 01:18:15,150
(However...)

1928
01:18:16,080 --> 01:18:17,819
(The ranch staff turn out to be tougher than expected.)

1929
01:18:17,820 --> 01:18:19,250
(Do something.)

1930
01:18:19,690 --> 01:18:21,190
(When the game is on, seniority means nothing.)

1931
01:18:21,990 --> 01:18:24,890
(A test of patience and a chorus of shouting)

1932
01:18:25,160 --> 01:18:26,559
(And)

1933
01:18:26,560 --> 01:18:27,889
(We've grown close to each other.)

1934
01:18:27,890 --> 01:18:30,559
(I will be sad when you leave.)

1935
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:32,700
(An unrevealed story)

1936
01:18:33,000 --> 01:18:35,899
(This is so annoying.)

1937
01:18:35,900 --> 01:18:39,910
(What's the reason behind Woo Bin's tears?)

1938
01:18:41,240 --> 01:18:44,009
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1939
01:18:44,010 --> 01:18:46,579
(Lee Kwang Soo)

1940
01:18:46,580 --> 01:18:48,819
(Kim Woo Bin)

1941
01:18:48,820 --> 01:18:50,880
(Doh Kyung Soo)

1942
01:18:55,520 --> 01:18:57,820
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)
